  31_have_black = False
  32try:
  33    # noinspection PyUnresolvedReferences
  34    import black

  37except ImportError:
  38    pass

  41# noinspection PyBroadException
  42def pretty_format_python(python_str: str, *, black_mode=None) -> str:
  43    """
  44    Format Python code, using black.
  45
  46    :param python_str: Python code
  47    :param black_mode: options for black
  48    :return: formatted Python code
  49    """
  50    assert isinstance(python_str, str)
  51    formatted_python = python_str
  52    if _have_black:
  53        try:
  54            if black_mode is None:
  55                black_mode = black.FileMode()
  56            formatted_python = black.format_str(python_str, mode=black_mode)
  57        except Exception:
  58            pass
  59    return formatted_python

  62def _assert_tables_defs_consistent(tm1: Dict, tm2: Dict):
  63    common_keys = set(tm1.keys()).intersection(tm2.keys())
  64    for k in common_keys:
  65        t1 = tm1[k]
  66        t2 = tm2[k]
  67        if not t1.same_table_description_(t2):
  68            raise ValueError("Table " + k + " has two incompatible representations")

  71def _convert_on_clause_to_parallel_lists(on) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
  72    on_a = []
  73    on_b = []
  74    if on is not None:
  75        if isinstance(on, str):
  76            on_a = [on]
  77            on_b = [on]
  78        elif isinstance(on, Iterable):
  79            if isinstance(on, Dict):
  80                on = list(on.items())
  81            else:
  82                on = list(on)
  83            for v in on :
  84                if isinstance(v, str):
  85                    on_a.append(v)
  86                    on_b.append(v)
  87                else:
  88                    v = list(v)
  89                    assert len(v) == 2
  90                    assert isinstance(v[0], str)
  91                    assert isinstance(v[1], str)
  92                    on_a.append(v[0])
  93                    on_b.append(v[1])
  94        else:
  95            raise ValueError(f"unexpected on-argument type {type(on)}")
  96    return on_a, on_b
  97
  98
  99def _convert_parallel_lists_to_on_clause(on_a: Iterable[str], on_b: Iterable[str]):
 100    assert isinstance(on_a, List)
 101    assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_a])
 102    assert isinstance(on_b, List)
 103    assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_b])
 104    assert len(on_a) == len(on_b)
 105    if len(on_a) <= 0:
 106        return []
 107    
 108    def enc_i(v_a, v_b):
 109        if v_a == v_b:
 110            return v_a
 111        return (v_a, v_b)
 112    
 113    return [enc_i(v_a, v_b) for v_a, v_b in zip(on_a, on_b)]
 114 
 115
 116def _work_col_group_arg(arg, *, arg_name: str, columns: Iterable[str]):
 117    """convert column list to standard form"""
 118    if arg is None:
 119        return []
 120    elif isinstance(arg, str):
 121        assert arg in set(columns)
 122        return [arg]
 123    elif isinstance(arg, Iterable):
 124        res = list(arg)
 125        assert len(res) == len(set(res))
 126        col_set = set(columns)
 127        assert numpy.all([col in col_set for col in arg])
 128        return res
 129    elif arg == 1:
 130        return 1
 131    assert ValueError(f"Need {arg_name} to be a list of strings or 1, got {arg}")

 134class ViewRepresentation(OperatorPlatform, abc.ABC):
 135    """Structure to represent the columns of a query or a table.
 136    Abstract base class."""
 137
 138    column_names: Tuple[str, ...]
 139    sources: Tuple[
 140        "ViewRepresentation", ...
 141    ]  # https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0484/#forward-references
 142
 143    def __init__(
 144        self,
 145        column_names: Iterable[str],
 146        *,
 147        sources: Optional[Iterable["ViewRepresentation"]] = None,
 148        node_name: str,
 149    ):
 150        # don't let instances masquerade as iterables
 151        assert not isinstance(column_names, str)
 152        assert not isinstance(sources, OperatorPlatform)
 153        if not isinstance(column_names, tuple):
 154            column_names = tuple(column_names)
 155        assert len(column_names) > 0
 156        for v in column_names:
 157            assert isinstance(v, str)
 158        assert len(column_names) == len(set(column_names))
 159        self.column_names = column_names
 160        if sources is None:
 161            sources = ()
 162        else:
 163            if not isinstance(sources, tuple):
 164                sources = tuple(sources)
 165        for si in sources:
 166            assert isinstance(si, ViewRepresentation)
 167        self.sources = sources
 168        OperatorPlatform.__init__(self, node_name=node_name)
 169
 170    def column_map(self) -> collections.OrderedDict:
 171        """
 172        Build a map of column names to ColumnReferences
 173        """
 174        res = collections.OrderedDict()
 175        for ci in self.column_names:
 176            res[ci] = data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference(self, ci)
 177        return res
 178
 179    def merged_rep_id(self) -> str:
 180        """
 181        String key for lookups.
 182        """
 183        return "ops+ " + str(id(self))
 184
 185    # convenience
 186
 187    def ex(self, *, data_model=None, narrow=True, allow_limited_tables=False):
 188        """
 189        Evaluate operators with respect to Pandas data frames already stored in the operator chain.
 190
 191        :param data_model: adaptor to data dialect (Pandas for now)
 192        :param narrow: logical, if True don't copy unexpected columns
 193        :param allow_limited_tables: logical, if True allow execution on non-complete tables
 194        :return: table result
 195        """
 196        tables = self.get_tables()
 197        data_map = dict()
 198        for tv in tables.values():
 199            assert isinstance(tv, TableDescription)
 200            assert tv.head is not None
 201            if len(tables) > 1:
 202                assert tv.table_name_was_set_by_user
 203            if not allow_limited_tables:
 204                assert tv.nrows == tv.head.shape[0]
 205            data_map[tv.table_name] = tv.head
 206        return self.eval(data_map=data_map, data_model=data_model, narrow=narrow)
 207
 208    # characterization
 209
 210    def get_tables(self):
 211        """Get a dictionary of all tables used in an operator DAG,
 212        raise an exception if the values are not consistent."""
 213
 214        tables = dict()
 215        # eliminate recursions by stepping through sources
 216        visit_stack = list()
 217        visit_stack.append(self)
 218        while len(visit_stack) > 0:
 219            cursor = visit_stack.pop()
 220            if isinstance(cursor, TableDescription):
 221                k = cursor.key
 222                v = cursor
 223                if k in tables.keys():
 224                    if not v.same_table_description_(tables[k]):
 225                        raise ValueError(
 226                            "Table " + k + " has two incompatible representations"
 227                        )
 228                else:
 229                    tables[k] = v
 230            else:
 231                for s in cursor.sources:
 232                    visit_stack.append(s)
 233        return tables
 234
 235    @abc.abstractmethod
 236    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List[str]:
 237        """
 238        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
 239
 240        :param using: optional column restriction.
 241        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
 242        """
 243
 244    def methods_used(self) -> Set[MethodUse]:
 245        """
 246        Return set of methods used.
 247        """
 248        res: Set[MethodUse] = set()
 249        self.get_method_uses_(res)
 250        return res
 251
 252    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
 253        """
 254        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
 255
 256        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
 257        :return: None
 258        """
 259        for s in self.sources:
 260            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
 261
 262    def columns_produced(self) -> List[str]:
 263        """Return list of columns produced by operator dag."""
 264        return list(self.column_names)
 265
 266    def columns_used_implementation_(
 267        self, *, using, columns_currently_using_records
 268    ) -> None:
 269        """Implementation of columns used calculation, internal method."""
 270        self_merged_rep_id = self.merged_rep_id()
 271        try:
 272            crec = columns_currently_using_records[self_merged_rep_id]
 273        except KeyError:
 274            crec = set()
 275            columns_currently_using_records[self_merged_rep_id] = crec
 276        if using is None:
 277            crec.update(self.column_names)
 278        else:
 279            unknown = set(using) - set(self.column_names)
 280            if len(unknown) > 0:
 281                raise ValueError("asked for unknown columns: " + str(unknown))
 282            crec.update(using)
 283        cu_list = self.columns_used_from_sources(crec.copy())
 284        for i in range(len(self.sources)):
 285            self.sources[i].columns_used_implementation_(
 286                using=cu_list[i],
 287                columns_currently_using_records=columns_currently_using_records,
 288            )
 289
 290    def columns_used(self, *, using=None) -> Dict:
 291        """Determine which columns are used from source tables."""
 292
 293        tables = self.get_tables()
 294        columns_currently_using_records = {
 295            v.merged_rep_id(): set() for v in tables.values()
 296        }
 297        self.columns_used_implementation_(
 298            using=using, columns_currently_using_records=columns_currently_using_records
 299        )
 300        columns_used = dict()
 301        for k, ti in tables.items():
 302            vi = columns_currently_using_records[ti.merged_rep_id()]
 303            columns_used[k] = vi.copy()
 304        return columns_used
 305
 306    def forbidden_columns(
 307        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
 308    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
 309        """
 310        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
 311        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
 312
 313        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
 314        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
 315        """
 316        if forbidden is None:
 317            forbidden = set()
 318        res: Dict[str, Set[str]] = dict()
 319        for source in self.sources:
 320            forbidden_i = source.forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
 321            for (tk, f) in forbidden_i.items():
 322                try:
 323                    have = res[tk]
 324                except KeyError:
 325                    have = set()
 326                    res[tk] = have
 327                have.update(f)
 328        return res
 329
 330    # printing
 331
 332    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True) -> str:
 333        """
 334        Return text representing operations. Internal method, allows skipping of sources.
 335
 336        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
 337        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
 338        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
 339        """
 340        return "ViewRepresentation(" + self.column_names.__repr__() + ")"
 341
 342    # noinspection PyBroadException
 343    def to_python(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, pretty=False, black_mode=None) -> str:
 344        """
 345        Return Python source code for operations.
 346
 347        :param indent: extra indent.
 348        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
 349        :param pretty: if True re-format result with black.
 350        :param black_mode: black formatter parameters.
 351        """
 352        self.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
 353        if pretty:
 354            strict = True
 355        python_str = (
 356            "(\n"
 357            + self.to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict, print_sources=True)
 358            + "\n)\n"
 359        )
 360        if pretty:
 361            python_str = pretty_format_python(python_str, black_mode=black_mode)
 362        return python_str
 363
 364    def __repr__(self):
 365        return self.to_python(strict=True, pretty=True)
 366
 367    def __str__(self):
 368        return self.to_python(strict=True, pretty=True)
 369
 370    # noinspection PyMethodMayBeStatic,PyUnusedLocal
 371    @abc.abstractmethod
 372    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
 373        """Check if immediate ops structure is equivalent, does not check child nodes"""
 374
 375    def __eq__(self, other):
 376        if not isinstance(other, ViewRepresentation):
 377            return False
 378        if not type(self) is type(other):
 379            return False
 380        if not type(other) is type(self):
 381            return False
 382        if self.node_name != other.node_name:
 383            return False
 384        if self.column_names != other.column_names:
 385            return False
 386        if len(self.sources) != len(other.sources):
 387            return False
 388        if not self._equiv_nodes(other):
 389            return False
 390        for i in range(len(self.sources)):
 391            if not self.sources[i].__eq__(other.sources[i]):
 392                return False
 393        return True
 394
 395    def __ne__(self, other):
 396        return not self.__eq__(other)
 397
 398    # query generation
 399
 400    @abc.abstractmethod
 401    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
 402        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
 403    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
 404        """
 405        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
 406
 407        :param db_model: database model
 408        :param using: optional column restriction set
 409        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
 410        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
 411        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
 412        """
 413
 414    def to_sql(
 415        self,
 416        db_model=None,
 417        *,
 418        sql_format_options=None,
 419    ) -> str:
 420        """
 421        Convert operator dag to SQL.
 422
 423        :param db_model: database model or handle data_algebra.db_model.DBModel or data_algebra.db_model.DBHandle
 424        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
 425        :return: string representation of SQL query
 426        """
 427        if db_model is None:
 428            import data_algebra.SQLite  # import late to avoid circular import issue
 429
 430            db_model = data_algebra.SQLite.SQLiteModel()
 431        return db_model.to_sql(
 432            ops=self,
 433            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
 434        )
 435
 436    # Pandas realization
 437
 438    def check_constraints(self, data_model, *, strict=True):
 439        """
 440        Check tables supplied meet data consistency constraints.
 441
 442        data_model: dictionary of column name lists.
 443        """
 444        self.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
 445        forbidden = self.forbidden_columns()
 446        tables = self.get_tables()
 447        missing_tables = set(tables.keys()) - set(data_model.keys())
 448        if len(missing_tables) > 0:
 449            raise ValueError("missing required tables: " + str(missing_tables))
 450        for k in tables.keys():
 451            have = set(data_model[k])
 452            td = tables[k]
 453            missing = set(td.column_names) - have
 454            if len(missing) > 0:
 455                raise ValueError(
 456                    "Table " + k + " missing required columns: " + str(missing)
 457                )
 458            if strict:
 459                cf = set(forbidden[k])
 460                excess = cf.intersection(have)
 461                if len(excess) > 0:
 462                    raise ValueError(
 463                        "Table " + k + " has forbidden columns: " + str(excess)
 464                    )
 465
 466    def eval(
 467        self,
 468        data_map,
 469        *,
 470        data_model=None,
 471        narrow: bool = True
 472    ):
 473        """
 474        Evaluate operators with respect to Pandas data frames.
 475
 476        :param data_map: map from table names to data frames
 477        :param data_model: adaptor to data dialect (Pandas for now)
 478        :param narrow: logical, if True don't copy unexpected columns
 479        :return: table result
 480        """
 481
 482        if data_map is not None:
 483            assert isinstance(data_map, dict)
 484        if data_model is None:
 485            data_model = data_algebra.default_data_model
 486        assert isinstance(data_model, data_algebra.data_model.DataModel)
 487        self.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
 488        tables = self.get_tables()
 489        self.check_constraints(
 490            {k: x.columns for (k, x) in data_map.items()}, strict=not narrow
 491        )
 492        for k in tables.keys():
 493            if k not in data_map.keys():
 494                raise ValueError("Required table " + k + " not in data_map")
 495            else:
 496                if not data_model.is_appropriate_data_instance(data_map[k]):
 497                    raise ValueError("data_map[" + k + "] was not a usable type")
 498        return data_model.eval(op=self, data_map=data_map, narrow=narrow)
 499
 500    # noinspection PyPep8Naming
 501    def transform(
 502        self,
 503        X,
 504        *,
 505        data_model=None,
 506        narrow: bool = True
 507    ):
 508        """
 509        Apply data transform to a table
 510
 511        :param X: tale to apply to
 512        :param data_model: data model for Pandas execution
 513        :param narrow: logical, if True narrow number of result columns to specification
 514        :return: transformed data frame
 515        """
 516        if data_model is None:
 517            data_model = data_algebra.default_data_model
 518        assert isinstance(data_model, data_algebra.data_model.DataModel)
 519        self.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
 520        tables = self.get_tables()
 521        if len(tables) != 1:
 522            raise ValueError(
 523                "transform(DataFrame) can only be applied to ops-dags with only one table def"
 524            )
 525        k = [k for k in tables.keys()][0]
 526        # noinspection PyUnresolvedReferences
 527        if not data_model.is_appropriate_data_instance(X):
 528            raise TypeError("can not apply transform() to type " + str(type(X)))
 529        data_map = {k: X}
 530        return self.eval(
 531            data_map=data_map,
 532            data_model=data_model,
 533            narrow=narrow
 534        )
 535
 536    # composition (used to eliminate intermediate order nodes)
 537
 538    def is_trivial_when_intermediate_(self) -> bool:
 539        """
 540        Return if True if operator can be eliminated from interior chain.
 541        """
 542        return False
 543
 544    # return table representation of self
 545    def as_table_description(self, table_name: str, *, qualifiers=None):
 546        """
 547        Return representation of operator as a table description.
 548
 549        :param table_name: table name to use.
 550        :param qualifiers: db qualifiers to annotate
 551        """
 552        return TableDescription(
 553            table_name=table_name,
 554            column_names=self.column_names,
 555            qualifiers=qualifiers,
 556        )
 557
 558    # implement builders for all non-initial ops types on base class
 559    def extend_parsed_(
 560        self, parsed_ops, *, partition_by=None, order_by=None, reverse=None
 561    ) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 562        """
 563        Add new derived columns, can replace existing columns for parsed operations. Internal method.
 564
 565        :param parsed_ops: dictionary of calculations to perform.
 566        :param partition_by: optional window partition specification, or 1.
 567        :param order_by: optional window ordering specification, or 1.
 568        :param reverse: optional order reversal specification.
 569        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 570        """
 571        if (parsed_ops is None) or (len(parsed_ops) < 1):
 572            return self
 573        partition_by = _work_col_group_arg(
 574            partition_by, arg_name="partition_by", columns=self.column_names
 575        )
 576        order_by = _work_col_group_arg(
 577            order_by, arg_name="order_by", columns=self.column_names
 578        )
 579        reverse = _work_col_group_arg(
 580            reverse, arg_name="reverse", columns=self.column_names
 581        )
 582        assert reverse != 1
 583        new_cols_produced_in_calc = set([k for k in parsed_ops.keys()])
 584        if (partition_by != 1) and (len(partition_by) > 0):
 585            if len(new_cols_produced_in_calc.intersection(partition_by)) > 0:
 586                raise ValueError("must not change partition_by columns")
 587            if (order_by != 1) and len(
 588                set(partition_by).intersection(set(order_by))
 589            ) > 0:
 590                raise ValueError("order_by and partition_by columns must be disjoint")
 591        if len(new_cols_produced_in_calc.intersection(order_by)) > 0:
 592            raise ValueError("must not change partition_by columns")
 593        if len(set(reverse).difference(order_by)) > 0:
 594            raise ValueError("all columns in reverse must be in order_by")
 595        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 596            return self.sources[0].extend_parsed_(
 597                parsed_ops=parsed_ops,
 598                partition_by=partition_by,
 599                order_by=order_by,
 600                reverse=reverse,
 601            )
 602        # see if we can combine nodes
 603        if isinstance(self, ExtendNode):
 604            compatible_partition = (partition_by == self.partition_by) or (
 605                ((partition_by == 1) or (len(partition_by) <= 0))
 606                and ((self.partition_by == 1) or (len(self.partition_by) <= 0))
 607            )
 608            same_windowing = (
 609                data_algebra.expr_rep.implies_windowed(parsed_ops)
 610                == self.windowed_situation
 611            )
 612            if (
 613                compatible_partition
 614                and same_windowing
 615                and (order_by == self.order_by)
 616                and (reverse == self.reverse)
 617            ):
 618                new_ops = data_algebra.data_ops_utils.try_to_merge_ops(
 619                    self.ops, parsed_ops
 620                )
 621                if new_ops is not None:
 622                    return ExtendNode(
 623                        source=self.sources[0],
 624                        parsed_ops=new_ops,
 625                        partition_by=partition_by,
 626                        order_by=order_by,
 627                        reverse=reverse,
 628                    )
 629        # new ops
 630        return ExtendNode(
 631            source=self,
 632            parsed_ops=parsed_ops,
 633            partition_by=partition_by,
 634            order_by=order_by,
 635            reverse=reverse,
 636        )
 637
 638    def extend(
 639        self, ops, *, partition_by=None, order_by=None, reverse=None
 640    ) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 641        """
 642        Add new derived columns, can replace existing columns.
 643
 644        :param ops: dictionary of calculations to perform.
 645        :param partition_by: optional window partition specification, or 1.
 646        :param order_by: optional window ordering specification, or 1.
 647        :param reverse: optional order reversal specification.
 648        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 649        """
 650        parsed_ops = data_algebra.expr_parse.parse_assignments_in_context(
 651            ops=ops, view=self
 652        )
 653        return self.extend_parsed_(
 654            parsed_ops=parsed_ops,
 655            partition_by=partition_by,
 656            order_by=order_by,
 657            reverse=reverse,
 658        )
 659
 660    def project_parsed_(
 661        self, parsed_ops=None, *, group_by=None
 662    ) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 663        """
 664        Compute projection, or grouped calculation for parsed ops. Internal method.
 665
 666        :param parsed_ops: dictionary of calculations to perform, can be empty.
 667        :param group_by: optional group key(s) specification.
 668        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 669        """
 670
 671        group_by = _work_col_group_arg(
 672            group_by, arg_name="group_by", columns=self.column_names
 673        )
 674        assert group_by != 1
 675        if ((parsed_ops is None) or (len(parsed_ops) < 1)) and (len(group_by) < 1):
 676            raise ValueError("project must have ops or group_by")
 677        new_cols_produced_in_calc = set([k for k in parsed_ops.keys()])
 678        if len(new_cols_produced_in_calc.intersection(group_by)):
 679            raise ValueError("project can not alter grouping columns")
 680        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 681            return self.sources[0].project_parsed_(parsed_ops, group_by=group_by)
 682        return ProjectNode(source=self, parsed_ops=parsed_ops, group_by=group_by)
 683
 684    def project(self, ops=None, *, group_by=None) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 685        """
 686        Compute projection, or grouped calculation.
 687
 688        :param ops: dictionary of calculations to perform, can be empty.
 689        :param group_by: optional group key(s) specification.
 690        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 691        """
 692        parsed_ops = data_algebra.expr_parse.parse_assignments_in_context(
 693            ops=ops, view=self
 694        )
 695        return self.project_parsed_(parsed_ops=parsed_ops, group_by=group_by)
 696
 697    def natural_join(
 698        self,
 699        b,
 700        *,
 701        on = None,
 702        jointype: str,
 703        check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec: bool = False,
 704        by = None,
 705        check_all_common_keys_in_by: bool = False,
 706    ) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 707        """
 708        Join self (left) results with b (right).
 709
 710        :param b: second or right table to join to.
 711        :param on: column names to enforce equality on (list of column names, list of tuples, or dictionary)
 712        :param jointype: name of join type.
 713        :param check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec: if True, raise if any non-equality key columns are common to tables.
 714        :param by: synonym for on, only set at most one of on or by (deprecated).
 715        :param check_all_common_keys_in_by: synonym for check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec (deprecated).
 716        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 717        """
 718        assert isinstance(b, ViewRepresentation)
 719        assert (on is None) or (by is None)
 720        if by is not None:
 721            on = by
 722        on_a, on_b = _convert_on_clause_to_parallel_lists(on)
 723        assert isinstance(jointype, str)
 724        assert isinstance(check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec, bool)
 725        assert isinstance(check_all_common_keys_in_by, bool)
 726        check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec = (
 727            check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec or check_all_common_keys_in_by
 728        )
 729        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 730            return self.sources[0].natural_join(b, on=on, jointype=jointype)
 731        return NaturalJoinNode(
 732            a=self,
 733            b=b,
 734            on_a=on_a,
 735            on_b=on_b,
 736            jointype=jointype,
 737            check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec=check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec,
 738        )
 739
 740    def concat_rows(
 741        self, b, *, id_column="source_name", a_name="a", b_name="b"
 742    ) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 743        """
 744        Union or concatenate rows of self with rows of b.
 745
 746        :param b: table with rows to add.
 747        :param id_column: optional name for new source identification column.
 748        :param a_name: source annotation to use for self/a.
 749        :param b_name: source annotation to use for b.
 750        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 751        """
 752        if b is None:
 753            return self
 754        assert isinstance(b, ViewRepresentation)
 755        assert isinstance(id_column, (str, type(None)))
 756        assert isinstance(a_name, str)
 757        assert isinstance(b_name, str)
 758        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 759            return self.sources[0].concat_rows(
 760                b, id_column=id_column, a_name=a_name, b_name=b_name
 761            )
 762        return ConcatRowsNode(
 763            a=self, b=b, id_column=id_column, a_name=a_name, b_name=b_name
 764        )
 765
 766    def select_rows_parsed_(self, parsed_expr) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 767        """
 768        Select rows matching parsed expr criteria. Internal method.
 769
 770        :param parsed_expr: logical expression specifying desired rows.
 771        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 772        """
 773        if parsed_expr is None:
 774            return self
 775        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 776            return self.sources[0].select_rows_parsed_(parsed_expr=parsed_expr)
 777        return SelectRowsNode(source=self, ops=parsed_expr)
 778
 779    def select_rows(self, expr) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 780        """
 781        Select rows matching expr criteria.
 782
 783        :param expr: logical expression specifying desired rows.
 784        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 785        """
 786        if expr is None:
 787            return self
 788        if isinstance(expr, (list, tuple)):
 789            # convert lists to and expressions
 790            assert all([isinstance(vi, str) for vi in expr])
 791            if len(expr) < 1:
 792                return self
 793            elif len(expr) == 1:
 794                expr = expr[0]
 795            else:
 796                expr = " and ".join(["(" + vi + ")" for vi in expr])
 797        assert isinstance(expr, (str, data_algebra.expr_rep.PreTerm))
 798        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 799            return self.sources[0].select_rows(expr)
 800        ops = data_algebra.expr_parse.parse_assignments_in_context(
 801            ops={"expr": expr}, view=self
 802        )
 803
 804        def r_walk_expr(opv):
 805            """recursively inspect expression types"""
 806            if not isinstance(opv, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
 807                return
 808            for oi in opv.args:
 809                r_walk_expr(oi)
 810
 811        for op in ops.values():
 812            r_walk_expr(op)
 813        return self.select_rows_parsed_(parsed_expr=ops)
 814
 815    def drop_columns(self, column_deletions) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 816        """
 817        Remove columns from result.
 818
 819        :param column_deletions: list of columns to remove.
 820        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 821        """
 822        if isinstance(column_deletions, str):
 823            column_deletions = [column_deletions]
 824        else:
 825            column_deletions = list(column_deletions)
 826        if (column_deletions is None) or (len(column_deletions) < 1):
 827            return self
 828        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 829            return self.sources[0].drop_columns(column_deletions)
 830        return DropColumnsNode(source=self, column_deletions=column_deletions)
 831
 832    def select_columns(self, columns) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 833        """
 834        Narrow to columns in result.
 835
 836        :param columns: list of columns to keep.
 837        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 838        """
 839        if isinstance(columns, str):
 840            columns = [columns]
 841        if (columns is None) or (len(columns) < 1):
 842            raise ValueError("must select at least one column")
 843        if columns == self.column_names:
 844            return self
 845        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 846            return self.sources[0].select_columns(columns)
 847        if isinstance(self, SelectColumnsNode):
 848            return self.sources[0].select_columns(columns)
 849        if isinstance(self, DropColumnsNode):
 850            return self.sources[0].select_columns(columns)
 851        return SelectColumnsNode(source=self, columns=columns)
 852
 853    def map_columns(self, column_remapping) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 854        """
 855        Map column names or rename.
 856
 857        :param column_remapping: dictionary mapping old column sources to new column names (same
 858                                 direction as Pandas rename).
 859        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 860        """
 861        if (column_remapping is None) or (len(column_remapping) < 1):
 862            return self
 863        assert isinstance(column_remapping, dict)
 864        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 865            return self.sources[0].map_columns(column_remapping)
 866        return MapColumnsNode(source=self, column_remapping=column_remapping)
 867
 868    def rename_columns(self, column_remapping) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 869        """
 870        Rename columns.
 871
 872        :param column_remapping: dictionary mapping new column names to old column sources (same
 873                                 direction as extend).
 874        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 875        """
 876        if (column_remapping is None) or (len(column_remapping) < 1):
 877            return self
 878        assert isinstance(column_remapping, dict)
 879        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 880            return self.sources[0].rename_columns(column_remapping)
 881        return RenameColumnsNode(source=self, column_remapping=column_remapping)
 882
 883    def order_rows(self, columns, *, reverse=None, limit=None) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 884        """
 885        Order rows by column set.
 886
 887        :param columns: columns to order by.
 888        :param reverse: optional columns to reverse order.
 889        :param limit: optional row limit to impose on result.
 890        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 891        """
 892        if isinstance(columns, str):
 893            columns = [columns]
 894        if isinstance(reverse, str):
 895            reverse = [reverse]
 896        if ((columns is None) or (len(columns) < 1)) and (limit is None):
 897            return self
 898        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 899            return self.sources[0].order_rows(columns, reverse=reverse, limit=limit)
 900        return OrderRowsNode(source=self, columns=columns, reverse=reverse, limit=limit)
 901
 902    def convert_records(self, record_map) -> "ViewRepresentation":
 903        """
 904        Apply a record mapping taking blocks_in to blocks_out structures.
 905
 906        :param record_map: data_algebra.cdata.RecordMap transform specification
 907        :return: compose operator directed acyclic graph
 908        """
 909        if record_map is None:
 910            return self
 911        if self.is_trivial_when_intermediate_():
 912            return self.sources[0].convert_records(record_map)
 913        return ConvertRecordsNode(source=self, record_map=record_map)
 914
 915
 916# Could also have general query as starting ops, but don't see a lot of point to
 917# it until somebody needs it.
 918
 919
 920class TableDescription(ViewRepresentation):
 921    """
 922     Describe columns, and qualifiers, of a table.
 923
 924    Example:
 925        from data_algebra.data_ops import *
 926        d = TableDescription(table_name='d', column_names=['x', 'y'])
 927        print(d)
 928    """
 929
 930    table_name: str
 931    column_names: Tuple[str, ...]
 932    qualifiers: Dict[str, str]
 933    key: str
 934    table_name_was_set_by_user: bool
 935
 936    def __init__(
 937        self,
 938        *,
 939        table_name: Optional[str] = None,
 940        column_names: Iterable[str],
 941        qualifiers=None,
 942        sql_meta=None,
 943        head=None,
 944        limit_was: Optional[int] = None,
 945        nrows: Optional[int] = None,
 946    ):
 947        if isinstance(column_names, str):
 948            column_names = (column_names,)
 949        else:
 950            column_names = tuple(
 951                column_names
 952            )  # convert to tuple from other types such as series
 953        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
 954            self, column_names=column_names, node_name="TableDescription"
 955        )
 956        if table_name is None:
 957            self.table_name_was_set_by_user = False
 958            table_name = "data_frame"
 959        else:
 960            self.table_name_was_set_by_user = True
 961        assert isinstance(table_name, str)
 962        if head is not None:
 963            if set([c for c in head.columns]) != set(column_names):
 964                raise ValueError("head.columns != column_names")
 965        self.head = head
 966        self.limit_was = limit_was
 967        self.sql_meta = sql_meta
 968        self.table_name = table_name
 969        self.nrows = nrows
 970        self.column_names = column_names
 971        if qualifiers is None:
 972            qualifiers = {}
 973        assert isinstance(qualifiers, dict)
 974        self.qualifiers = qualifiers.copy()
 975        self.key = ""
 976        if self.table_name is not None:
 977            self.key = self.table_name
 978
 979    def same_table_description_(self, other):
 980        """
 981        Return true if other is a description of the same table. Internal method, ingores data.
 982        """
 983        if not isinstance(other, data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription):
 984            return False
 985        if self.table_name_was_set_by_user != other.table_name_was_set_by_user:
 986            return False
 987        if self.table_name != other.table_name:
 988            return False
 989        if self.key != other.key:
 990            return False
 991        if self.column_names != other.column_names:
 992            return False
 993        if self.qualifiers != other.qualifiers:
 994            return False
 995        # ignore head and limit_was, as they are just advisory
 996        return True
 997
 998    def merged_rep_id(self) -> str:
 999        """
1000        String key for lookups.
1001        """
1002        return "table_" + str(self.key)
1003
1004    def forbidden_columns(
1005        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1006    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1007        """
1008        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1009        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1010
1011        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1012        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1013        """
1014        if forbidden is None:
1015            forbidden = set()
1016        return {self.key: set(forbidden)}
1017
1018    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1019        """
1020        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1021
1022        :param a: operators to apply to
1023        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1024        :return: new operator DAG
1025        """
1026        if (target_table_key is None) or (target_table_key == self.key):
1027            # replace table with a
1028            return a
1029        # copy self
1030        r = TableDescription(
1031            table_name=self.table_name,
1032            column_names=self.column_names,
1033            qualifiers=self.qualifiers,
1034        )
1035        return r
1036
1037    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1038        if not isinstance(other, TableDescription):
1039            return False
1040        if not self.table_name == other.table_name:
1041            return False
1042        if not self.column_names == other.column_names:
1043            return False
1044        if not self.qualifiers == other.qualifiers:
1045            return False
1046        if not self.key == other.key:
1047            return False
1048        return True
1049
1050    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1051        """
1052        Return text representing operations.
1053
1054        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1055        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1056        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1057        """
1058        spacer = " "
1059        if indent >= 0:
1060            spacer = "\n " + " " * indent
1061        column_limit = 20
1062        truncated = (not strict) and (column_limit < len(self.column_names))
1063        if truncated:
1064            cols_to_print = [
1065                self.column_names[i].__repr__() for i in range(column_limit)
1066            ] + ["+ " + str(len(self.column_names)) + " more"]
1067        else:
1068            cols_to_print = [c.__repr__() for c in self.column_names]
1069        col_text = data_algebra.flow_text.flow_text(
1070            cols_to_print, align_right=70 - max(0, indent), sep_width=2
1071        )
1072        col_text = [", ".join(line) for line in col_text]
1073        col_text = (",  " + spacer).join(col_text)
1074        s = (
1075            "TableDescription("
1076            + spacer
1077            + "table_name="
1078            + self.table_name.__repr__()
1079            + ","
1080            + spacer
1081            + "column_names=["
1082            + spacer
1083            + "  "
1084            + col_text
1085            + "]"
1086        )
1087        if len(self.qualifiers) > 0:
1088            s = s + "," + spacer + "qualifiers=" + self.qualifiers.__repr__()
1089        s = s + ")"
1090        return s
1091
1092    def get_tables(self):
1093        """get a dictionary of all tables used in an operator DAG,
1094        raise an exception if the values are not consistent"""
1095        return {self.key: self}
1096
1097    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1098        """
1099        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1100
1101        :param using: optional column restriction.
1102        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1103        """
1104        return []  # no inputs to table description
1105
1106    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1107        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1108    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1109        """
1110        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1111
1112        :param db_model: database model
1113        :param using: optional column restriction set
1114        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1115        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1116        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
1117        """
1118        return db_model.table_def_to_near_sql(
1119            self,
1120            using=using,
1121            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1122            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1123        )
1124
1125    def __str__(self):
1126        rep = ViewRepresentation.__str__(self)
1127        if self.head is not None:
1128            rep = rep + "\n#\t" + str(self.head).replace("\n", "\n#\t")
1129        return rep
1130
1131    # comparable to other table descriptions
1132    def __eq__(self, other):
1133        if not isinstance(other, TableDescription):
1134            return False
1135        return self.key.__eq__(other.key)
1136
1137    def __hash__(self):
1138        return self.key.__hash__()
1139
1140
1141def describe_table(
1142    d,
1143    table_name=None,
1144    *,
1145    qualifiers=None,
1146    sql_meta=None,
1147    row_limit: Optional[int] = 7,
1148    keep_sample=True,
1149    keep_all=False,
1150) -> TableDescription:
1151    """
1152    :param d: pandas table to describe
1153    :param table_name: name of table
1154    :param qualifiers: optional, able qualifiers
1155    :param sql_meta: optional, sql meta information map
1156    :param row_limit: how many rows to sample
1157    :param keep_sample: logical, if True retain head of table
1158    :param keep_all: logical, if True retain all of table
1159    :return: TableDescription
1160    """
1161    assert not isinstance(d, OperatorPlatform)
1162    assert not isinstance(d, ViewRepresentation)
1163    column_names = [c for c in d.columns]
1164    head = None
1165    nrows = d.shape[0]
1166    if keep_all or (row_limit is None):
1167        row_limit = None
1168        head = d.copy()
1169        head.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
1170    elif keep_sample:
1171        if nrows > row_limit:
1172            head = d.iloc[range(row_limit), :].copy()
1173        else:
1174            head = d.copy()
1175        head.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
1176    return TableDescription(
1177        table_name=table_name,
1178        column_names=column_names,
1179        qualifiers=qualifiers,
1180        sql_meta=sql_meta,
1181        head=head,
1182        limit_was=row_limit,
1183        nrows=nrows,
1184    )
1185
1186
1187def table(d, *, table_name=None):
1188    """
1189    Capture a table for later use
1190
1191    :param d: Pandas data frame to capture
1192    :param table_name: name for this table
1193    :return: a table description, with values retained
1194    """
1195    return describe_table(
1196        d=d,
1197        table_name=table_name,
1198        qualifiers=None,
1199        sql_meta=None,
1200        row_limit=None,
1201        keep_sample=True,
1202        keep_all=True,
1203    )
1204
1205
1206def descr(**kwargs):
1207    """
1208    Capture a named partial table as a description.
1209
1210    :param kwargs: exactly one named table of the form table_name=table_value
1211    :return: a table description (not all values retained)
1212    """
1213    assert len(kwargs) == 1
1214    table_name = [k for k in kwargs.keys()][0]
1215    d = kwargs[table_name]
1216    return describe_table(
1217        d=d,
1218        table_name=table_name,
1219        qualifiers=None,
1220        sql_meta=None,
1221        row_limit=7,
1222        keep_sample=True,
1223        keep_all=False,
1224    )
1225
1226
1227def data(*args, **kwargs):
1228    """
1229    Capture a full table for later use. Exactly one of args/kwags can be set.
1230
1231    :param args: at most one unnamed table of the form table_name=table_value
1232    :param kwargs: at most one named table of the form table_name=table_value
1233    :return: a table description, with all values retained
1234    """
1235    assert (len(args) + len(kwargs)) == 1
1236    if len(kwargs) == 1:
1237        table_name = [k for k in kwargs.keys()][0]
1238        d = kwargs[table_name]
1239        return table(d=d, table_name=table_name)
1240    d = args[0]
1241    return table(d=d, table_name=None)
1242
1243
1244class ExtendNode(ViewRepresentation):
1245    """
1246    Class representation of .extend() method/step.
1247    """
1248
1249    windowed_situation: bool
1250    ordered_windowed_situation: bool
1251    partition_by: List[str]
1252
1253    def __init__(
1254        self, *, source, parsed_ops, partition_by=None, order_by=None, reverse=None
1255    ):
1256        windowed_situation = data_algebra.expr_rep.implies_windowed(parsed_ops)
1257        ordered_windowed_situation = False
1258        self.ops = parsed_ops
1259        if partition_by is None:
1260            partition_by = []
1261        if isinstance(partition_by, numbers.Number):
1262            partition_by = []
1263            windowed_situation = True
1264        if isinstance(partition_by, str):
1265            partition_by = [partition_by]
1266        if len(partition_by) > 0:
1267            windowed_situation = True
1268        self.partition_by = partition_by
1269        if order_by is None:
1270            order_by = []
1271        if isinstance(order_by, str):
1272            order_by = [order_by]
1273        if len(order_by) > 0:
1274            windowed_situation = True
1275            ordered_windowed_situation = True
1276        self.windowed_situation = windowed_situation
1277        self.order_by = order_by
1278        if reverse is None:
1279            reverse = []
1280        if isinstance(reverse, str):
1281            reverse = [reverse]
1282        self.reverse = reverse
1283        column_names = list(source.column_names)
1284        consumed_cols = set()
1285        for (k, o) in parsed_ops.items():
1286            o.get_column_names(consumed_cols)
1287        unknown_cols = consumed_cols - set(source.column_names)
1288        if len(unknown_cols) > 0:
1289            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(unknown_cols))
1290        known_cols = set(column_names)
1291        for ci in parsed_ops.keys():
1292            if ci not in known_cols:
1293                column_names.append(ci)
1294        if len(partition_by) != len(set(partition_by)):
1295            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in partition_by")
1296        if len(order_by) != len(set(order_by)):
1297            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in order_by")
1298        if len(reverse) != len(set(reverse)):
1299            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in reverse")
1300        unknown = set(partition_by) - known_cols
1301        if len(unknown) > 0:
1302            raise ValueError("unknown partition_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1303        unknown = set(order_by) - known_cols
1304        if len(unknown) > 0:
1305            raise ValueError("unknown order_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1306        unknown = set(reverse) - set(order_by)
1307        if len(unknown) > 0:
1308            raise ValueError("reverse columns not in order_by: " + str(unknown))
1309        bad_overwrite = set(parsed_ops.keys()).intersection(
1310            set(partition_by).union(order_by, reverse)
1311        )
1312        if len(bad_overwrite) > 0:
1313            raise ValueError("tried to change: " + str(bad_overwrite))
1314        # check op arguments are very simple: all arguments are column names
1315        if windowed_situation:
1316            source_col_set = set(source.column_names)
1317            for (k, opk) in parsed_ops.items():
1318                if not isinstance(opk, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1319                    raise ValueError(
1320                        "non-aggregated expression in windowed/partitioned extend: "
1321                        + "'"
1322                        + k
1323                        + "': '"
1324                        + str(opk)
1325                        + "'"
1326                    )
1327                if len(opk.args) > 1:
1328                    for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1329                        if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1330                            raise ValueError(
1331                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1332                                + "'"
1333                                + k
1334                                + "': '"
1335                                + str(opk)
1336                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1337                            )
1338                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1339                    if isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1340                        value_name = opk.args[0].column_name
1341                        if value_name not in source_col_set:
1342                            raise ValueError(value_name + " not in source column set")
1343                    else:
1344                        if not isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1345                            raise ValueError(
1346                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1347                                + "'"
1348                                + k
1349                                + "': '"
1350                                + str(opk)
1351                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1352                            )
1353                if windowed_situation and (
1354                    opk.op
1355                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_windowed_situation
1356                ):
1357                    raise ValueError(
1358                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in a windowed situation"
1359                    )
1360                if ordered_windowed_situation and (
1361                    opk.op
1362                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_ordered_windowed_situation
1363                ):
1364                    raise ValueError(
1365                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in an ordered windowed situation"
1366                    )
1367                if (not ordered_windowed_situation) and (
1368                    opk.op
1369                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_imply_ordered_windowed_situation
1370                ):
1371                    raise ValueError(
1372                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in not-ordered windowed situation"
1373                    )
1374        self.ordered_windowed_situation = ordered_windowed_situation
1375        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1376            self, column_names=column_names, sources=[source], node_name="ExtendNode"
1377        )
1378
1379    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1380        """
1381        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1382
1383        :param a: operators to apply to
1384        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1385        :return: new operator DAG
1386        """
1387        new_sources = [
1388            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1389        ]
1390        return new_sources[0].extend_parsed_(
1391            parsed_ops=self.ops,
1392            partition_by=self.partition_by,
1393            order_by=self.order_by,
1394            reverse=self.reverse,
1395        )
1396
1397    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1398        if not isinstance(other, ExtendNode):
1399            return False
1400        if not self.windowed_situation == other.windowed_situation:
1401            return False
1402        if not self.partition_by == other.partition_by:
1403            return False
1404        if not self.order_by == other.order_by:
1405            return False
1406        if not self.reverse == other.reverse:
1407            return False
1408        if set(self.ops.keys()) != set(other.ops.keys()):
1409            return False
1410        for k in self.ops.keys():
1411            if not self.ops[k].is_equal(other.ops[k]):
1412                return False
1413        return True
1414
1415    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
1416        """
1417        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
1418
1419        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
1420        :return: None
1421        """
1422        for s in self.sources:
1423            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1424        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1425        for opk in self.ops.values():
1426            opk.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1427        for k in method_names_seen:
1428            methods_seen.add(
1429                MethodUse(
1430                    k,
1431                    is_project=False,
1432                    is_windowed=self.windowed_situation,
1433                    is_ordered=self.ordered_windowed_situation,
1434                )
1435            )
1436
1437    def check_extend_window_fns_(self):
1438        """
1439        Confirm extend functions are all compatible with windowing in Pandas. Internal function.
1440        """
1441        window_situation = (len(self.partition_by) > 0) or (len(self.order_by) > 0)
1442        if window_situation:
1443            # check these are forms we are prepared to work with
1444            for (k, opk) in self.ops.items():
1445                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1446                    if len(opk.args) > 1:
1447                        for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1448                            if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1449                                raise ValueError(
1450                                    "window function with more than one non-value argument"
1451                                )
1452                    for i in range(len(opk.args)):
1453                        if not (
1454                            isinstance(
1455                                opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference
1456                            )
1457                            or isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value)
1458                        ):
1459                            raise ValueError(
1460                                "window expression argument must be a column or value: "
1461                                + str(k)
1462                                + ": "
1463                                + str(opk)
1464                            )
1465
1466    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1467        """
1468        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1469
1470        :param using: optional column restriction.
1471        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1472        """
1473        if using is None:
1474            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1475        subops = {k: op for (k, op) in self.ops.items() if k in using}
1476        if len(subops) <= 0:
1477            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1478        columns_we_take = using.union(self.partition_by, self.order_by, self.reverse)
1479        columns_we_take = columns_we_take - subops.keys()
1480        for (k, o) in subops.items():
1481            o.get_column_names(columns_we_take)
1482        return [
1483            OrderedSet(
1484                [v for v in self.sources[0].column_names if v in columns_we_take]
1485            )
1486        ]
1487
1488    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1489        """
1490        Return text representing operations.
1491
1492        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1493        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1494        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1495        """
1496        spacer = " "
1497        if indent >= 0:
1498            spacer = "\n   " + " " * indent
1499        s = ""
1500        if print_sources:
1501            s = self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict) + spacer
1502        ops = [
1503            k.__repr__() + ": " + opi.to_python().__repr__()
1504            for (k, opi) in self.ops.items()
1505        ]
1506        flowed = ("," + spacer + " ").join(ops)
1507        s = s + (".extend({" + spacer + " " + flowed + "}")
1508        if self.windowed_situation:
1509            if len(self.partition_by) > 0:
1510                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=" + self.partition_by.__repr__()
1511            else:
1512                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=1"
1513        if len(self.order_by) > 0:
1514            s = s + "," + spacer + "order_by=" + self.order_by.__repr__()
1515        if len(self.reverse) > 0:
1516            s = s + "," + spacer + "reverse=" + self.reverse.__repr__()
1517        s = s + ")"
1518        return s
1519
1520    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1521        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1522    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1523        """
1524        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1525
1526        :param db_model: database model
1527        :param using: optional column restriction set
1528        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1529        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1530        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
1531        """
1532        return db_model.extend_to_near_sql(
1533            self,
1534            using=using,
1535            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1536            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1537        )
1538
1539
1540class ProjectNode(ViewRepresentation):
1541    """
1542    Class representation of .project() method/step.
1543    """
1544
1545    # TODO: should project to take an optional order for last() style calculations?
1546    def __init__(self, *, source, parsed_ops, group_by=None):
1547        self.ops = parsed_ops
1548        if group_by is None:
1549            group_by = []
1550        if isinstance(group_by, str):
1551            group_by = [group_by]
1552        self.group_by = group_by
1553        column_names = group_by.copy()
1554        consumed_cols = set()
1555        for c in group_by:
1556            consumed_cols.add(c)
1557        for (k, o) in parsed_ops.items():
1558            o.get_column_names(consumed_cols)
1559        unknown_cols = consumed_cols - set(source.column_names)
1560        if len(unknown_cols) > 0:
1561            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(unknown_cols))
1562        known_cols = set(column_names)
1563        for ci in parsed_ops.keys():
1564            if ci not in known_cols:
1565                column_names.append(ci)
1566        if len(group_by) != len(set(group_by)):
1567            raise ValueError("Duplicate name in group_by")
1568        unknown = set(group_by) - known_cols
1569        if len(unknown) > 0:
1570            raise ValueError("unknown group_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1571        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1572            self, column_names=column_names, sources=[source], node_name="ProjectNode"
1573        )
1574        for (k, opk) in self.ops.items():
1575            if isinstance(opk, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1576                if len(opk.args) > 1:
1577                    raise ValueError(
1578                        "non-trivial aggregation expression: "
1579                        + str(k)
1580                        + ": "
1581                        + str(opk)
1582                    )
1583                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1584                    if not (
1585                        isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference)
1586                        or isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value)
1587                    ):
1588                        raise ValueError(
1589                            "windows expression argument must be a column or value: "
1590                            + str(k)
1591                            + ": "
1592                            + str(opk)
1593                        )
1594                if (
1595                    opk.op
1596                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_imply_ordered_windowed_situation
1597                ):
1598                    raise ValueError(str(opk) + "' is not allowed in project")
1599                if opk.op in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_not_allowed_in_project:
1600                    raise ValueError(str(opk) + "' is not allowed in project")
1601            else:
1602                raise ValueError(
1603                    "non-aggregated expression in project: " + str(k) + ": " + str(opk)
1604                )
1605            # TODO: check op is in list of aggregators
1606            # Note: non-aggregators making through will be caught by table shape check
1607
1608    def forbidden_columns(
1609        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1610    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1611        """
1612        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1613        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1614
1615        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1616        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1617        """
1618        if forbidden is None:
1619            forbidden = set()
1620        forbidden = set(forbidden).intersection(self.column_names)
1621        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
1622
1623    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
1624        """
1625        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
1626
1627        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
1628        :return: None
1629        """
1630        for s in self.sources:
1631            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1632        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1633        for opk in self.ops.values():
1634            opk.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1635        for k in method_names_seen:
1636            methods_seen.add(
1637                MethodUse(k, is_project=True, is_windowed=False, is_ordered=False)
1638            )
1639
1640    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1641        """
1642        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1643
1644        :param a: operators to apply to
1645        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1646        :return: new operator DAG
1647        """
1648        new_sources = [
1649            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1650        ]
1651        return new_sources[0].project_parsed_(
1652            parsed_ops=self.ops, group_by=self.group_by
1653        )
1654
1655    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1656        if not isinstance(other, ProjectNode):
1657            return False
1658        if not self.group_by == other.group_by:
1659            return False
1660        if set(self.ops.keys()) != set(other.ops.keys()):
1661            return False
1662        for k in self.ops.keys():
1663            if not self.ops[k].is_equal(other.ops[k]):
1664                return False
1665        return True
1666
1667    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1668        """
1669        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1670
1671        :param using: optional column restriction.
1672        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1673        """
1674        if using is None:
1675            subops = self.ops
1676        else:
1677            subops = {k: op for (k, op) in self.ops.items() if k in using}
1678        columns_we_take = set(self.group_by)
1679        for (k, o) in subops.items():
1680            o.get_column_names(columns_we_take)
1681        return [columns_we_take]
1682
1683    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1684        """
1685        Return text representing operations.
1686
1687        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1688        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1689        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1690        """
1691        spacer = " "
1692        if indent >= 0:
1693            spacer = "\n   " + " " * indent
1694        s = ""
1695        if print_sources:
1696            s = (
1697                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
1698                + "\n"
1699                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
1700            )
1701        s = s + (
1702            ".project({"
1703            + spacer
1704            + " "
1705            + ("," + spacer + " ").join(
1706                [
1707                    k.__repr__() + ": " + opi.to_python().__repr__()
1708                    for (k, opi) in self.ops.items()
1709                ]
1710            )
1711            + "}"
1712        )
1713        if len(self.group_by) > 0:
1714            s = s + "," + spacer + "group_by=" + self.group_by.__repr__()
1715        s = s + ")"
1716        return s
1717
1718    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1719        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1720    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1721        """
1722        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1723
1724        :param db_model: database model
1725        :param using: optional column restriction set
1726        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1727        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1728        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
1729        """
1730        return db_model.project_to_near_sql(
1731            self,
1732            using=using,
1733            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1734            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1735        )
1736
1737
1738class SelectRowsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1739    """
1740    Class representation of .select() method/step.
1741    """
1742
1743    expr: data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression
1744    decision_columns: Set[str]
1745
1746    def __init__(self, source, ops):
1747        if len(ops) < 1:
1748            raise ValueError("no ops")
1749        if len(ops) > 1:
1750            raise ValueError("too many ops")
1751        self.ops = ops
1752        self.expr = ops["expr"]
1753        self.decision_columns = set()
1754        self.expr.get_column_names(self.decision_columns)
1755        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1756            self,
1757            column_names=source.column_names,
1758            sources=[source],
1759            node_name="SelectRowsNode",
1760        )
1761
1762    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
1763        """
1764        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
1765
1766        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
1767        :return: None
1768        """
1769        for s in self.sources:
1770            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1771        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1772        self.expr.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1773        for k in method_names_seen:
1774            methods_seen.add(
1775                MethodUse(k, is_project=False, is_windowed=False, is_ordered=False)
1776            )
1777
1778    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1779        """
1780        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1781
1782        :param a: operators to apply to
1783        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1784        :return: new operator DAG
1785        """
1786        new_sources = [
1787            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1788        ]
1789        return new_sources[0].select_rows_parsed_(parsed_ops=self.ops)
1790
1791    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1792        if not isinstance(other, SelectRowsNode):
1793            return False
1794        if not self.expr.is_equal(other.expr):
1795            return False
1796        if len(self.ops) != len(other.ops):
1797            return False
1798        return True
1799
1800    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1801        """
1802        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1803
1804        :param using: optional column restriction.
1805        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1806        """
1807        columns_we_take = OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)
1808        if using is None:
1809            return [columns_we_take]
1810        columns_we_take = ordered_intersect(columns_we_take, using)
1811        columns_we_take = ordered_union(columns_we_take, self.decision_columns)
1812        return [columns_we_take]
1813
1814    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1815        """
1816        Return text representing operations.
1817
1818        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1819        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1820        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1821        """
1822        s = ""
1823        if print_sources:
1824            s = (
1825                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)

1852class SelectColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1853    """
1854    Class representation of .select_columns() method/step.
1855    """
1856
1857    column_selection: List[str]
1858
1859    def __init__(self, source, columns):
1860        if isinstance(columns, str):
1861            columns = [columns]
1862        column_selection = [c for c in columns]
1863        self.column_selection = column_selection
1864        if len(column_selection) < 1:
1865            raise ValueError("can not drop all columns")
1866        unknown = set(column_selection) - set(source.column_names)
1867        if len(unknown) > 0:
1868            raise KeyError("selecting unknown columns " + str(unknown))
1869        if isinstance(source, SelectColumnsNode):
1870            source = source.sources[0]
1871        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1872            self,
1873            column_names=column_selection,
1874            sources=[source],
1875            node_name="SelectColumnsNode",
1876        )
1877
1878    def forbidden_columns(
1879        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1880    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1881        """
1882        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1883        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1884
1885        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1886        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1887        """
1888        if forbidden is None:
1889            forbidden = set()
1890        forbidden = set(forbidden).intersection(self.column_selection)
1891        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
1892
1893    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1894        """
1895        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1896
1897        :param a: operators to apply to
1898        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1899        :return: new operator DAG
1900        """
1901        new_sources = [
1902            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1903        ]
1904        return new_sources[0].select_columns(columns=self.column_selection)
1905
1906    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1907        if not isinstance(other, SelectColumnsNode):
1908            return False
1909        if not self.column_selection == other.column_selection:
1910            return False
1911        return True
1912
1913    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1914        """
1915        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1916
1917        :param using: optional column restriction.
1918        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1919        """
1920        cols = set(self.column_selection.copy())
1921        if using is None:
1922            return [cols]
1923        return [cols.intersection(using)]
1924
1925    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1926        """
1927        Return text representing operations.
1928
1929        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1930        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1931        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1932        """
1933        s = ""
1934        if print_sources:
1935            s = (
1936                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
1937                + "\n"
1938                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
1939            )
1940        s = s + (".select_columns(" + self.column_selection.__repr__() + ")")
1941        return s
1942
1943    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1944        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1945    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1946        """
1947        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1948
1949        :param db_model: database model
1950        :param using: optional column restriction set
1951        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1952        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1953        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL

1955        return db_model.select_columns_to_near_sql(
1956            self,
1957            using=using,
1958            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1959            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,

1963class DropColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1964    """
1965    Class representation of .drop_columns() method/step.
1966    """
1967
1968    column_deletions: List[str]
1969
1970    def __init__(self, source, column_deletions):
1971        if isinstance(column_deletions, str):
1972            column_deletions = [column_deletions]
1973        column_deletions = [c for c in column_deletions]
1974        self.column_deletions = column_deletions
1975        unknown = set(column_deletions) - set(source.column_names)
1976        if len(unknown) > 0:
1977            raise KeyError("dropping unknown columns " + str(unknown))
1978        remaining_columns = [
1979            c for c in source.column_names if c not in column_deletions
1980        ]
1981        if len(remaining_columns) < 1:
1982            raise ValueError("can not drop all columns")
1983        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1984            self,
1985            column_names=remaining_columns,
1986            sources=[source],
1987            node_name="DropColumnsNode",

1995        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1996
1997        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1998        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1999        """
2000        if forbidden is None:
2001            forbidden = set()
2002        forbidden = set(forbidden) - set(self.column_deletions)
2003        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
2004
2005    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2006        """
2007        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
