class TableDescription(ViewRepresentation): 
 921class TableDescription(ViewRepresentation):
 922    """
 923     Describe columns, and qualifiers, of a table.
 924
 925    Example:
 926        from data_algebra.data_ops import *
 927        d = TableDescription(table_name='d', column_names=['x', 'y'])
 928        print(d)
 929    """
 930
 931    table_name: str
 932    column_names: Tuple[str, ...]
 933    qualifiers: Dict[str, str]
 934    key: str
 935    table_name_was_set_by_user: bool
 936
 937    def __init__(
 938        self,
 939        *,
 940        table_name: Optional[str] = None,
 941        column_names: Iterable[str],
 942        qualifiers=None,
 943        sql_meta=None,
 944        head=None,
 945        limit_was: Optional[int] = None,
 946        nrows: Optional[int] = None,
 947    ):
 948        if isinstance(column_names, str):
 949            column_names = (column_names,)
 950        else:
 951            column_names = tuple(
 952                column_names
 953            )  # convert to tuple from other types such as series
 954        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
 955            self, column_names=column_names, node_name="TableDescription"
 956        )
 957        if table_name is None:
 958            self.table_name_was_set_by_user = False
 959            table_name = "data_frame"
 960        else:
 961            self.table_name_was_set_by_user = True
 962        assert isinstance(table_name, str)
 963        if head is not None:
 964            if set([c for c in head.columns]) != set(column_names):
 965                raise ValueError("head.columns != column_names")
 966        self.head = head
 967        self.limit_was = limit_was
 968        self.sql_meta = sql_meta
 969        self.table_name = table_name
 970        self.nrows = nrows
 971        self.column_names = column_names
 972        if qualifiers is None:
 973            qualifiers = {}
 974        assert isinstance(qualifiers, dict)
 975        self.qualifiers = qualifiers.copy()
 976        self.key = ""
 977        if self.table_name is not None:
 978            self.key = self.table_name
 979
 980    def same_table_description_(self, other):
 981        """
 982        Return true if other is a description of the same table. Internal method, ingores data.
 983        """
 984        if not isinstance(other, data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription):
 985            return False
 986        if self.table_name_was_set_by_user != other.table_name_was_set_by_user:
 987            return False
 988        if self.table_name != other.table_name:
 989            return False
 990        if self.key != other.key:
 991            return False
 992        if self.column_names != other.column_names:
 993            return False
 994        if self.qualifiers != other.qualifiers:
 995            return False
 996        # ignore head and limit_was, as they are just advisory
 997        return True
 998
 999    def merged_rep_id(self) -> str:
1000        """
1001        String key for lookups.
1002        """
1003        return "table_" + str(self.key)
1004
1005    def forbidden_columns(
1006        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1007    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1008        """
1009        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1010        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1011
1012        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1013        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1014        """
1015        if forbidden is None:
1016            forbidden = set()
1017        return {self.key: set(forbidden)}
1018
1019    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1020        """
1021        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1022
1023        :param a: operators to apply to
1024        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1025        :return: new operator DAG
1026        """
1027        if (target_table_key is None) or (target_table_key == self.key):
1028            # replace table with a
1029            return a
1030        # copy self
1031        r = TableDescription(
1032            table_name=self.table_name,
1033            column_names=self.column_names,
1034            qualifiers=self.qualifiers,
1035        )
1036        return r
1037
1038    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1039        if not isinstance(other, TableDescription):
1040            return False
1041        if not self.table_name == other.table_name:
1042            return False
1043        if not self.column_names == other.column_names:
1044            return False
1045        if not self.qualifiers == other.qualifiers:
1046            return False
1047        if not self.key == other.key:
1048            return False
1049        return True
1050
1051    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1052        """
1053        Return text representing operations.
1054
1055        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1056        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1057        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1058        """
1059        spacer = " "
1060        if indent >= 0:
1061            spacer = "\n " + " " * indent
1062        column_limit = 20
1063        truncated = (not strict) and (column_limit < len(self.column_names))
1064        if truncated:
1065            cols_to_print = [
1066                self.column_names[i].__repr__() for i in range(column_limit)
1067            ] + ["+ " + str(len(self.column_names)) + " more"]
1068        else:
1069            cols_to_print = [c.__repr__() for c in self.column_names]
1070        col_text = data_algebra.flow_text.flow_text(
1071            cols_to_print, align_right=70 - max(0, indent), sep_width=2
1072        )
1073        col_text = [", ".join(line) for line in col_text]
1074        col_text = (",  " + spacer).join(col_text)
1075        s = (
1076            "TableDescription("
1077            + spacer
1078            + "table_name="
1079            + self.table_name.__repr__()
1080            + ","
1081            + spacer
1082            + "column_names=["
1083            + spacer
1084            + "  "
1085            + col_text
1086            + "]"
1087        )
1088        if len(self.qualifiers) > 0:
1089            s = s + "," + spacer + "qualifiers=" + self.qualifiers.__repr__()
1090        s = s + ")"
1091        return s
1092
1093    def get_tables(self):
1094        """get a dictionary of all tables used in an operator DAG,
1095        raise an exception if the values are not consistent"""
1096        return {self.key: self}
1097
1098    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1099        """
1100        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1101
1102        :param using: optional column restriction.
1103        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1104        """
1105        return []  # no inputs to table description
1106
1107    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1108        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1109    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1110        """
1111        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1112
1113        :param db_model: database model
1114        :param using: optional column restriction set
1115        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1116        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1117        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
1118        """
1119        return db_model.table_def_to_near_sql(
1120            self,
1121            using=using,
1122            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1123            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1124        )
1125
1126    def __str__(self):
1127        rep = ViewRepresentation.__str__(self)
1128        if self.head is not None:
1129            rep = rep + "\n#\t" + str(self.head).replace("\n", "\n#\t")
1130        return rep
1131
1132    # comparable to other table descriptions
1133    def __eq__(self, other):
1134        if not isinstance(other, TableDescription):
1135            return False
1136        return self.key.__eq__(other.key)
1137
1138    def __hash__(self):
1139        return self.key.__hash__()

def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True): 
1051    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1052        """
1053        Return text representing operations.
1054
1055        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1056        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1057        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1058        """
1059        spacer = " "
1060        if indent >= 0:
1061            spacer = "\n " + " " * indent
1062        column_limit = 20
1063        truncated = (not strict) and (column_limit < len(self.column_names))
1064        if truncated:
1065            cols_to_print = [
1066                self.column_names[i].__repr__() for i in range(column_limit)
1067            ] + ["+ " + str(len(self.column_names)) + " more"]
1068        else:
1069            cols_to_print = [c.__repr__() for c in self.column_names]
1070        col_text = data_algebra.flow_text.flow_text(
1071            cols_to_print, align_right=70 - max(0, indent), sep_width=2
1072        )
1073        col_text = [", ".join(line) for line in col_text]
1074        col_text = (",  " + spacer).join(col_text)
1075        s = (
1076            "TableDescription("
1077            + spacer
1078            + "table_name="
1079            + self.table_name.__repr__()
1080            + ","
1081            + spacer
1082            + "column_names=["
1083            + spacer
1084            + "  "
1085            + col_text
1086            + "]"
1087        )
1088        if len(self.qualifiers) > 0:
1089            s = s + "," + spacer + "qualifiers=" + self.qualifiers.__repr__()
1090        s = s + ")"
1091        return s

Return text representing operations.

def describe_table( d, table_name=None, *, qualifiers=None, sql_meta=None, row_limit: Optional[int] = 7, keep_sample=True, keep_all=False) -> data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription: 
1142def describe_table(
1143    d,
1144    table_name=None,
1145    *,
1146    qualifiers=None,
1147    sql_meta=None,
1148    row_limit: Optional[int] = 7,
1149    keep_sample=True,
1150    keep_all=False,
1151) -> TableDescription:
1152    """
1153    :param d: pandas table to describe
1154    :param table_name: name of table
1155    :param qualifiers: optional, able qualifiers
1156    :param sql_meta: optional, sql meta information map
1157    :param row_limit: how many rows to sample
1158    :param keep_sample: logical, if True retain head of table
1159    :param keep_all: logical, if True retain all of table
1160    :return: TableDescription
1161    """
1162    assert not isinstance(d, OperatorPlatform)
1163    assert not isinstance(d, ViewRepresentation)
1164    column_names = [c for c in d.columns]
1165    head = None
1166    nrows = d.shape[0]
1167    if keep_all or (row_limit is None):
1168        row_limit = None
1169        head = d.copy()
1170        head.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
1171    elif keep_sample:
1172        if nrows > row_limit:
1173            head = d.iloc[range(row_limit), :].copy()
1174        else:
1175            head = d.copy()
1176        head.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
1177    return TableDescription(
1178        table_name=table_name,
1179        column_names=column_names,
1180        qualifiers=qualifiers,
1181        sql_meta=sql_meta,
1182        head=head,
1183        limit_was=row_limit,
1184        nrows=nrows,
1185    )

class ExtendNode(ViewRepresentation): 
1245class ExtendNode(ViewRepresentation):
1246    """
1247    Class representation of .extend() method/step.
1248    """
1249
1250    windowed_situation: bool
1251    ordered_windowed_situation: bool
1252    partition_by: List[str]
1253
1254    def __init__(
1255        self, *, source, parsed_ops, partition_by=None, order_by=None, reverse=None
1256    ):
1257        windowed_situation = data_algebra.expr_rep.implies_windowed(parsed_ops)
1258        ordered_windowed_situation = False
1259        self.ops = parsed_ops
1260        if partition_by is None:
1261            partition_by = []
1262        if isinstance(partition_by, numbers.Number):
1263            partition_by = []
1264            windowed_situation = True
1265        if isinstance(partition_by, str):
1266            partition_by = [partition_by]
1267        if len(partition_by) > 0:
1268            windowed_situation = True
1269        self.partition_by = partition_by
1270        if order_by is None:
1271            order_by = []
1272        if isinstance(order_by, str):
1273            order_by = [order_by]
1274        if len(order_by) > 0:
1275            windowed_situation = True
1276            ordered_windowed_situation = True
1277        self.windowed_situation = windowed_situation
1278        self.order_by = order_by
1279        if reverse is None:
1280            reverse = []
1281        if isinstance(reverse, str):
1282            reverse = [reverse]
1283        self.reverse = reverse
1284        column_names = list(source.column_names)
1285        consumed_cols = set()
1286        for (k, o) in parsed_ops.items():
1287            o.get_column_names(consumed_cols)
1288        unknown_cols = consumed_cols - set(source.column_names)
1289        if len(unknown_cols) > 0:
1290            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(unknown_cols))
1291        known_cols = set(column_names)
1292        for ci in parsed_ops.keys():
1293            if ci not in known_cols:
1294                column_names.append(ci)
1295        if len(partition_by) != len(set(partition_by)):
1296            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in partition_by")
1297        if len(order_by) != len(set(order_by)):
1298            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in order_by")
1299        if len(reverse) != len(set(reverse)):
1300            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in reverse")
1301        unknown = set(partition_by) - known_cols
1302        if len(unknown) > 0:
1303            raise ValueError("unknown partition_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1304        unknown = set(order_by) - known_cols
1305        if len(unknown) > 0:
1306            raise ValueError("unknown order_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1307        unknown = set(reverse) - set(order_by)
1308        if len(unknown) > 0:
1309            raise ValueError("reverse columns not in order_by: " + str(unknown))
1310        bad_overwrite = set(parsed_ops.keys()).intersection(
1311            set(partition_by).union(order_by, reverse)
1312        )
1313        if len(bad_overwrite) > 0:
1314            raise ValueError("tried to change: " + str(bad_overwrite))
1315        # check op arguments are very simple: all arguments are column names
1316        if windowed_situation:
1317            source_col_set = set(source.column_names)
1318            for (k, opk) in parsed_ops.items():
1319                if not isinstance(opk, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1320                    raise ValueError(
1321                        "non-aggregated expression in windowed/partitioned extend: "
1322                        + "'"
1323                        + k
1324                        + "': '"
1325                        + str(opk)
1326                        + "'"
1327                    )
1328                if len(opk.args) > 1:
1329                    for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1330                        if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1331                            raise ValueError(
1332                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1333                                + "'"
1334                                + k
1335                                + "': '"
1336                                + str(opk)
1337                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1338                            )
1339                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1340                    if isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1341                        value_name = opk.args[0].column_name
1342                        if value_name not in source_col_set:
1343                            raise ValueError(value_name + " not in source column set")
1344                    else:
1345                        if not isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1346                            raise ValueError(
1347                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1348                                + "'"
1349                                + k
1350                                + "': '"
1351                                + str(opk)
1352                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1353                            )
1354                if windowed_situation and (
1355                    opk.op
1356                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_windowed_situation
1357                ):
1358                    raise ValueError(
1359                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in a windowed situation"
1360                    )
1361                if ordered_windowed_situation and (
1362                    opk.op
1363                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_ordered_windowed_situation
1364                ):
1365                    raise ValueError(
1366                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in an ordered windowed situation"
1367                    )
1368                if (not ordered_windowed_situation) and (
1369                    opk.op
1370                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_imply_ordered_windowed_situation
1371                ):
1372                    raise ValueError(
1373                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in not-ordered windowed situation"
1374                    )
1375        self.ordered_windowed_situation = ordered_windowed_situation
1376        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1377            self, column_names=column_names, sources=[source], node_name="ExtendNode"
1378        )
1379
1380    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1381        """
1382        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1383
1384        :param a: operators to apply to
1385        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1386        :return: new operator DAG
1387        """
1388        new_sources = [
1389            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1390        ]
1391        return new_sources[0].extend_parsed_(
1392            parsed_ops=self.ops,
1393            partition_by=self.partition_by,
1394            order_by=self.order_by,
1395            reverse=self.reverse,
1396        )
1397
1398    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1399        if not isinstance(other, ExtendNode):
1400            return False
1401        if not self.windowed_situation == other.windowed_situation:
1402            return False
1403        if not self.partition_by == other.partition_by:
1404            return False
1405        if not self.order_by == other.order_by:
1406            return False
1407        if not self.reverse == other.reverse:
1408            return False
1409        if set(self.ops.keys()) != set(other.ops.keys()):
1410            return False
1411        for k in self.ops.keys():
1412            if not self.ops[k].is_equal(other.ops[k]):
1413                return False
1414        return True
1415
1416    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
1417        """
1418        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
1419
1420        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
1421        :return: None
1422        """
1423        for s in self.sources:
1424            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1425        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1426        for opk in self.ops.values():
1427            opk.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1428        for k in method_names_seen:
1429            methods_seen.add(
1430                MethodUse(
1431                    k,
1432                    is_project=False,
1433                    is_windowed=self.windowed_situation,
1434                    is_ordered=self.ordered_windowed_situation,
1435                )
1436            )
1437
1438    def check_extend_window_fns_(self):
1439        """
1440        Confirm extend functions are all compatible with windowing in Pandas. Internal function.
1441        """
1442        window_situation = (len(self.partition_by) > 0) or (len(self.order_by) > 0)
1443        if window_situation:
1444            # check these are forms we are prepared to work with
1445            for (k, opk) in self.ops.items():
1446                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1447                    if len(opk.args) > 1:
1448                        for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1449                            if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1450                                raise ValueError(
1451                                    "window function with more than one non-value argument"
1452                                )
1453                    for i in range(len(opk.args)):
1454                        if not (
1455                            isinstance(
1456                                opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference
1457                            )
1458                            or isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value)
1459                        ):
1460                            raise ValueError(
1461                                "window expression argument must be a column or value: "
1462                                + str(k)
1463                                + ": "
1464                                + str(opk)
1465                            )
1466
1467    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1468        """
1469        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1470
1471        :param using: optional column restriction.
1472        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1473        """
1474        if using is None:
1475            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1476        subops = {k: op for (k, op) in self.ops.items() if k in using}
1477        if len(subops) <= 0:
1478            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1479        columns_we_take = using.union(self.partition_by, self.order_by, self.reverse)
1480        columns_we_take = columns_we_take - subops.keys()
1481        for (k, o) in subops.items():
1482            o.get_column_names(columns_we_take)
1483        return [
1484            OrderedSet(
1485                [v for v in self.sources[0].column_names if v in columns_we_take]
1486            )
1487        ]
1488
1489    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1490        """
1491        Return text representing operations.
1492
1493        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1494        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1495        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1496        """
1497        spacer = " "
1498        if indent >= 0:
1499            spacer = "\n   " + " " * indent
1500        s = ""
1501        if print_sources:
1502            s = self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict) + spacer
1503        ops = [
1504            k.__repr__() + ": " + opi.to_python().__repr__()
1505            for (k, opi) in self.ops.items()
1506        ]
1507        flowed = ("," + spacer + " ").join(ops)
1508        s = s + (".extend({" + spacer + " " + flowed + "}")
1509        if self.windowed_situation:
1510            if len(self.partition_by) > 0:
1511                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=" + self.partition_by.__repr__()
1512            else:
1513                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=1"
1514        if len(self.order_by) > 0:
1515            s = s + "," + spacer + "order_by=" + self.order_by.__repr__()
1516        if len(self.reverse) > 0:
1517            s = s + "," + spacer + "reverse=" + self.reverse.__repr__()
1518        s = s + ")"
1519        return s
1520
1521    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1522        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
1523    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1524        """
1525        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
1526
1527        :param db_model: database model
1528        :param using: optional column restriction set
1529        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1530        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
1531        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
1532        """
1533        return db_model.extend_to_near_sql(
1534            self,
1535            using=using,
1536            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1537            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1538        )

Class representation of .extend() method/step.

1277        self.windowed_situation = windowed_situation
1278        self.order_by = order_by
1279        if reverse is None:
1280            reverse = []
1281        if isinstance(reverse, str):
1282            reverse = [reverse]
1283        self.reverse = reverse
1284        column_names = list(source.column_names)
1285        consumed_cols = set()
1286        for (k, o) in parsed_ops.items():
1287            o.get_column_names(consumed_cols)
1288        unknown_cols = consumed_cols - set(source.column_names)
1289        if len(unknown_cols) > 0:
1290            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(unknown_cols))
1291        known_cols = set(column_names)
1292        for ci in parsed_ops.keys():
1293            if ci not in known_cols:
1294                column_names.append(ci)
1295        if len(partition_by) != len(set(partition_by)):
1296            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in partition_by")
1297        if len(order_by) != len(set(order_by)):
1298            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in order_by")
1299        if len(reverse) != len(set(reverse)):
1300            raise ValueError("Duplicate name(s) in reverse")
1301        unknown = set(partition_by) - known_cols
1302        if len(unknown) > 0:
1303            raise ValueError("unknown partition_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1304        unknown = set(order_by) - known_cols
1305        if len(unknown) > 0:
1306            raise ValueError("unknown order_by columns: " + str(unknown))
1307        unknown = set(reverse) - set(order_by)
1308        if len(unknown) > 0:
1309            raise ValueError("reverse columns not in order_by: " + str(unknown))
1310        bad_overwrite = set(parsed_ops.keys()).intersection(
1311            set(partition_by).union(order_by, reverse)
1312        )
1313        if len(bad_overwrite) > 0:
1314            raise ValueError("tried to change: " + str(bad_overwrite))
1315        # check op arguments are very simple: all arguments are column names
1316        if windowed_situation:
1317            source_col_set = set(source.column_names)
1318            for (k, opk) in parsed_ops.items():
1319                if not isinstance(opk, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1320                    raise ValueError(
1321                        "non-aggregated expression in windowed/partitioned extend: "
1322                        + "'"
1323                        + k
1324                        + "': '"
1325                        + str(opk)
1326                        + "'"
1327                    )
1328                if len(opk.args) > 1:
1329                    for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1330                        if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1331                            raise ValueError(
1332                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1333                                + "'"
1334                                + k
1335                                + "': '"
1336                                + str(opk)
1337                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1338                            )
1339                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1340                    if isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1341                        value_name = opk.args[0].column_name
1342                        if value_name not in source_col_set:
1343                            raise ValueError(value_name + " not in source column set")
1344                    else:
1345                        if not isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1346                            raise ValueError(
1347                                "in windowed situations only simple operators are allowed, "
1348                                + "'"
1349                                + k
1350                                + "': '"
1351                                + str(opk)
1352                                + "' term is too complex an expression"
1353                            )
1354                if windowed_situation and (
1355                    opk.op
1356                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_windowed_situation
1357                ):
1358                    raise ValueError(
1359                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in a windowed situation"
1360                    )
1361                if ordered_windowed_situation and (
1362                    opk.op
1363                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_contradict_ordered_windowed_situation
1364                ):
1365                    raise ValueError(
1366                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in an ordered windowed situation"
1367                    )
1368                if (not ordered_windowed_situation) and (
1369                    opk.op
1370                    in data_algebra.expr_rep.fn_names_that_imply_ordered_windowed_situation
1371                ):
1372                    raise ValueError(
1373                        str(opk) + "' is not allowed in not-ordered windowed situation"
1374                    )
1375        self.ordered_windowed_situation = ordered_windowed_situation
1376        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1377            self, column_names=column_names, sources=[source], node_name="ExtendNode"
1378        )
def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None): 
1380    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1381        """
1382        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1383
1384        :param a: operators to apply to
1385        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1386        :return: new operator DAG
1387        """
1388        new_sources = [
1389            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1390        ]
1391        return new_sources[0].extend_parsed_(
1392            parsed_ops=self.ops,
1393            partition_by=self.partition_by,
1394            order_by=self.order_by,
1395            reverse=self.reverse,
1396        )

def check_extend_window_fns_(self): 
1438    def check_extend_window_fns_(self):
1439        """
1440        Confirm extend functions are all compatible with windowing in Pandas. Internal function.
1441        """
1442        window_situation = (len(self.partition_by) > 0) or (len(self.order_by) > 0)
1443        if window_situation:
1444            # check these are forms we are prepared to work with
1445            for (k, opk) in self.ops.items():
1446                if len(opk.args) > 0:
1447                    if len(opk.args) > 1:
1448                        for i in range(1, len(opk.args)):
1449                            if not isinstance(opk.args[i], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1450                                raise ValueError(
1451                                    "window function with more than one non-value argument"
1452                                )
1453                    for i in range(len(opk.args)):
1454                        if not (
1455                            isinstance(
1456                                opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference
1457                            )
1458                            or isinstance(opk.args[0], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value)
1459                        ):
1460                            raise ValueError(
1461                                "window expression argument must be a column or value: "
1462                                + str(k)
1463                                + ": "
1464                                + str(opk)
1465                            )

Confirm extend functions are all compatible with windowing in Pandas. Internal function.

def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List: 
1467    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1468        """
1469        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1470
1471        :param using: optional column restriction.
1472        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1473        """
1474        if using is None:
1475            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1476        subops = {k: op for (k, op) in self.ops.items() if k in using}
1477        if len(subops) <= 0:
1478            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)]
1479        columns_we_take = using.union(self.partition_by, self.order_by, self.reverse)
1480        columns_we_take = columns_we_take - subops.keys()
1481        for (k, o) in subops.items():
1482            o.get_column_names(columns_we_take)
1483        return [
1484            OrderedSet(
1485                [v for v in self.sources[0].column_names if v in columns_we_take]
1486            )
1487        ]

Get columns used from sources. Internal method.

def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True): 
1489    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1490        """
1491        Return text representing operations.
1492
1493        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1494        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1495        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1496        """
1497        spacer = " "
1498        if indent >= 0:
1499            spacer = "\n   " + " " * indent
1500        s = ""
1501        if print_sources:
1502            s = self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict) + spacer
1503        ops = [
1504            k.__repr__() + ": " + opi.to_python().__repr__()
1505            for (k, opi) in self.ops.items()
1506        ]
1507        flowed = ("," + spacer + " ").join(ops)
1508        s = s + (".extend({" + spacer + " " + flowed + "}")
1509        if self.windowed_situation:
1510            if len(self.partition_by) > 0:
1511                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=" + self.partition_by.__repr__()
1512            else:
1513                s = s + "," + spacer + "partition_by=1"
1514        if len(self.order_by) > 0:
1515            s = s + "," + spacer + "order_by=" + self.order_by.__repr__()
1516        if len(self.reverse) > 0:
1517            s = s + "," + spacer + "reverse=" + self.reverse.__repr__()
1518        s = s + ")"
1519        return s

Return text representing operations.

1656    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1657        if not isinstance(other, ProjectNode):
1658            return False
1659        if not self.group_by == other.group_by:
1660            return False
1661        if set(self.ops.keys()) != set(other.ops.keys()):
1662            return False
1663        for k in self.ops.keys():
1664            if not self.ops[k].is_equal(other.ops[k]):
1665                return False
1666        return True

1630        """
1631        for s in self.sources:
1632            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1633        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1634        for opk in self.ops.values():
1635            opk.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1636        for k in method_names_seen:
1637            methods_seen.add(
1638                MethodUse(k, is_project=True, is_windowed=False, is_ordered=False)
1639            )

Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.

:params methods_seen: set to collect results in.

Returns

None

1643        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.

def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List: 
1668    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1669        """
1670        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1671
1672        :param using: optional column restriction.
1673        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1674        """
1675        if using is None:
1676            subops = self.ops
1677        else:
1678            subops = {k: op for (k, op) in self.ops.items() if k in using}
1679        columns_we_take = set(self.group_by)
1680        for (k, o) in subops.items():
1681            o.get_column_names(columns_we_take)
1682        return [columns_we_take]

def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True): 
1684    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1685        """
1686        Return text representing operations.
1687
1688        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1689        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1690        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1691        """
1692        spacer = " "
1693        if indent >= 0:
1694            spacer = "\n   " + " " * indent
1695        s = ""
1696        if print_sources:
1697            s = (
1698                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
1699                + "\n"
1700                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
1701            )
1702        s = s + (
1703            ".project({"
1704            + spacer
1705            + " "
1706            + ("," + spacer + " ").join(
1707                [
1708                    k.__repr__() + ": " + opi.to_python().__repr__()
1709                    for (k, opi) in self.ops.items()
1710                ]
1711            )
1712            + "}"
1713        )
1714        if len(self.group_by) > 0:
1715            s = s + "," + spacer + "group_by=" + self.group_by.__repr__()
1716        s = s + ")"
1717        return s

  • strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.

class SelectRowsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
1739class SelectRowsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1740    """
1741    Class representation of .select() method/step.
1742    """
1743
1744    expr: data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression
1745    decision_columns: Set[str]
1746
1747    def __init__(self, source, ops):
1748        if len(ops) < 1:
1749            raise ValueError("no ops")
1750        if len(ops) > 1:
1751            raise ValueError("too many ops")
1752        self.ops = ops
1753        self.expr = ops["expr"]
1754        self.decision_columns = set()
1755        self.expr.get_column_names(self.decision_columns)
1756        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1757            self,
1758            column_names=source.column_names,
1759            sources=[source],
1760            node_name="SelectRowsNode",
1761        )
1762
1763    def get_method_uses_(self, methods_seen: Set[MethodUse]) -> None:
1764        """
1765        Implementation of get methods_used(), internal method.
1766
1767        :params methods_seen: set to collect results in.
1768        :return: None
1769        """
1770        for s in self.sources:
1771            s.get_method_uses_(methods_seen)
1772        method_names_seen: Set[str] = set()
1773        self.expr.get_method_names(method_names_seen)
1774        for k in method_names_seen:
1775            methods_seen.add(
1776                MethodUse(k, is_project=False, is_windowed=False, is_ordered=False)
1777            )
1778
1779    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1780        """
1781        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1782
1783        :param a: operators to apply to
1784        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1785        :return: new operator DAG
1786        """
1787        new_sources = [
1788            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1789        ]
1790        return new_sources[0].select_rows_parsed_(parsed_ops=self.ops)
1791
1792    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1793        if not isinstance(other, SelectRowsNode):
1794            return False
1795        if not self.expr.is_equal(other.expr):
1796            return False
1797        if len(self.ops) != len(other.ops):
1798            return False
1799        return True
1800
1801    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1802        """
1803        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1804
1805        :param using: optional column restriction.
1806        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1807        """
1808        columns_we_take = OrderedSet(self.sources[0].column_names)
1809        if using is None:
1810            return [columns_we_take]
1811        columns_we_take = ordered_intersect(columns_we_take, using)
1812        columns_we_take = ordered_union(columns_we_take, self.decision_columns)
1813        return [columns_we_take]
1814

1822        """

1827                + "\n"
1828                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
1829            )
1830        s = s + (".select_rows(" + self.expr.to_python().__repr__() + ")")
1831        return s

class SelectColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
1853class SelectColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1854    """
1855    Class representation of .select_columns() method/step.
1856    """
1857
1858    column_selection: List[str]
1859
1860    def __init__(self, source, columns):
1861        if isinstance(columns, str):
1862            columns = [columns]
1863        column_selection = [c for c in columns]
1864        self.column_selection = column_selection
1865        if len(column_selection) < 1:
1866            raise ValueError("can not drop all columns")
1867        unknown = set(column_selection) - set(source.column_names)
1868        if len(unknown) > 0:
1869            raise KeyError("selecting unknown columns " + str(unknown))
1870        if isinstance(source, SelectColumnsNode):
1871            source = source.sources[0]
1872        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1873            self,
1874            column_names=column_selection,
1875            sources=[source],
1876            node_name="SelectColumnsNode",
1877        )
1878
1879    def forbidden_columns(
1880        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1881    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1882        """
1883        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1884        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1885
1886        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1887        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
1888        """
1889        if forbidden is None:
1890            forbidden = set()
1891        forbidden = set(forbidden).intersection(self.column_selection)
1892        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
1893
1894    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
1895        """
1896        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
1897
1898        :param a: operators to apply to
1899        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
1900        :return: new operator DAG
1901        """
1902        new_sources = [
1903            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
1904        ]
1905        return new_sources[0].select_columns(columns=self.column_selection)
1906
1907    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
1908        if not isinstance(other, SelectColumnsNode):
1909            return False
1910        if not self.column_selection == other.column_selection:
1911            return False
1912        return True
1913
1914    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
1915        """
1916        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
1917
1918        :param using: optional column restriction.
1919        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
1920        """
1921        cols = set(self.column_selection.copy())
1922        if using is None:
1923            return [cols]
1924        return [cols.intersection(using)]
1925
1926    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
1927        """
1928        Return text representing operations.
1929
1930        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
1931        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
1932        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
1933        """
1934        s = ""
1935        if print_sources:
1936            s = (
1937                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
1938                + "\n"
1939                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
1940            )
1941        s = s + (".select_columns(" + self.column_selection.__repr__() + ")")
1942        return s
1943
1944    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
1945        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None

1952        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
1953        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting

1957            self,
1958            using=using,
1959            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
1960            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1961        )

class DropColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
1964class DropColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
1965    """
1966    Class representation of .drop_columns() method/step.
1967    """
1968
1969    column_deletions: List[str]
1970
1971    def __init__(self, source, column_deletions):
1972        if isinstance(column_deletions, str):
1973            column_deletions = [column_deletions]
1974        column_deletions = [c for c in column_deletions]
1975        self.column_deletions = column_deletions
1976        unknown = set(column_deletions) - set(source.column_names)
1977        if len(unknown) > 0:
1978            raise KeyError("dropping unknown columns " + str(unknown))
1979        remaining_columns = [
1980            c for c in source.column_names if c not in column_deletions
1981        ]
1982        if len(remaining_columns) < 1:
1983            raise ValueError("can not drop all columns")
1984        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
1985            self,
1986            column_names=remaining_columns,
1987            sources=[source],
1988            node_name="DropColumnsNode",
1989        )
1990
1991    def forbidden_columns(
1992        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
1993    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
1994        """
1995        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
1996        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
1997
1998        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
1999        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
2000        """
2001        if forbidden is None:
2002            forbidden = set()
2003        forbidden = set(forbidden) - set(self.column_deletions)
2004        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=forbidden)
2005
2006    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2007        """
2008        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
2009
2010        :param a: operators to apply to
2011        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
2012        :return: new operator DAG
2013        """
2014        new_sources = [
2015            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
2016        ]
2017        return new_sources[0].drop_columns(column_deletions=self.column_deletions)
2018
2019    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
2020        if not isinstance(other, DropColumnsNode):
2021            return False
2022        if not self.column_deletions == other.column_deletions:
2023            return False
2024        return True
2025
2026    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
2027        """
2028        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
2029
2030        :param using: optional column restriction.
2031        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
2032        """
2033        if using is None:
2034            using = set(self.sources[0].column_names)
2035        return [set([c for c in using if c not in self.column_deletions])]
2036
2037    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
2038        """
2039        Return text representing operations.
2040
2041        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
2042        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
2043        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
2044        """
2045        s = ""
2046        if print_sources:
2047            s = (
2048                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
2049                + "\n"
2050                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
2051            )
2052        s = s + (".drop_columns(" + self.column_deletions.__repr__() + ")")
2053        return s
2054
2055    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
2056        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
2057    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
2058        """
2059        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
2060
2061        :param db_model: database model
2062        :param using: optional column restriction set
2063        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
2064        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
2065        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
2066        """
2067        return db_model.drop_columns_to_near_sql(
2068            self,
2069            using=using,
2070            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
2071            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,

2088            reverse = []

2090            reverse = [reverse]

2095        if len(unknown) > 0:
2096            raise ValueError("missing required columns: " + str(unknown))

2098        if len(not_order) > 0:
2099            raise ValueError("columns declared reverse, but not order: " + str(unknown))

class MapColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
2197class MapColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
2198    """
2199    Class representation of .map_columns() method/step.
2200    """
2201
2202    column_remapping: Dict[str, str]
2203    column_deletions: List[str]
2204
2205    def __init__(self, source, column_remapping):
2206        self.column_remapping = {k: v for (k, v) in column_remapping.items() if v is not None}
2207        self.column_deletions = [k for (k, v) in column_remapping.items() if v is None]
2208        new_cols = [v for (k, v) in column_remapping.items() if v is not None]
2209        orig_cols = [k for k in column_remapping.keys()]
2210        unknown = set(orig_cols) - set(source.column_names)
2211        if len(unknown) > 0:
2212            raise ValueError("Tried to rename unknown columns: " + str(unknown))
2213        collisions = (
2214            set(source.column_names) - set(new_cols).intersection(orig_cols)
2215        ).intersection(new_cols)
2216        if len(collisions) > 0:
2217            raise ValueError(
2218                "Mapping "
2219                + str(self.column_remapping)
2220                + " collides with existing columns "
2221                + str(collisions)
2222            )
2223        column_names = [
2224            (k if k not in self.column_remapping.keys() else self.column_remapping[k])
2225            for k in source.column_names
2226        ]
2227        self.new_columns = set(new_cols) - set(orig_cols)
2228        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2229            self,
2230            column_names=column_names,
2231            sources=[source],
2232            node_name="MapColumnsNode",
2233        )
2234
2235    def forbidden_columns(
2236        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
2237    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:
2238        """
2239        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
2240        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).
2241
2242        :param forbidden: optional incoming forbids.
2243        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.
2244        """
2245        # this is where forbidden columns are introduced
2246        if forbidden is None:
2247            forbidden = set()
2248        new_forbidden = set(forbidden) - self.column_remapping.keys()
2249        new_forbidden.update(self.new_columns)
2250        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=new_forbidden)
2251
2252    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2253        """
2254        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
2255
2256        :param a: operators to apply to
2257        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
2258        :return: new operator DAG
2259        """
2260        new_sources = [
2261            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
2262        ]
2263        return new_sources[0].map_columns(column_remapping=self.column_remapping)
2264
2265    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
2266        if not isinstance(other, MapColumnsNode):
2267            return False
2268        if not (self.column_remapping == other.column_remapping):
2269            return False
2270        if not (self.column_deletions == other.column_deletions):
2271            return False
2272        return True
2273
2274    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
2275        """
2276        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
2277
2278        :param using: optional column restriction.
2279        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
2280        """
2281        if using is None:
2282            using_tuple = self.column_names
2283        else:
2284            using_tuple = tuple(using)
2285        cols = [k for k in using_tuple if k ]
2286        reverse_mapping = {v: k for k, v in self.column_remapping.items()}
2287        rev_keys = set(reverse_mapping.keys())
2288        cols = [
2289            (k if k not in rev_keys else reverse_mapping[k])
2290            for k in using_tuple
2291        ] + self.column_deletions
2292        return [OrderedSet(cols)]
2293
2294    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
2295        """
2296        Return text representing operations.
2297
2298        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
2299        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
2300        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
2301        """
2302        s = ""
2303        if print_sources:
2304            s = (
2305                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
2306                + "\n"
2307                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
2308            )
2309        column_remapping = self.column_remapping.copy()
2310        column_remapping.update({k: None for k in self.column_deletions})
2311        s = s + (".map_columns(" + column_remapping.__repr__() + ")")
2312        return s
2313
2314    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
2315        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
2316    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
2317        """
2318        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
2319
2320        :param db_model: database model
2321        :param using: optional column restriction set
2322        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
2323        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
2324        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
2325        """
2326        return db_model.map_columns_to_near_sql(
2327            self,
2328            using=using,
2329            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
2330            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
2331        )

class RenameColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
2334class RenameColumnsNode(ViewRepresentation):
2335    """
2336    Class representation of .rename_columns() method/step.
2337    """
2338
2339    column_remapping: Dict[str, str]
2340    reverse_mapping: Dict[str, str]
2341
2342    def __init__(self, source, column_remapping):
2343        self.column_remapping = column_remapping.copy()
2344        self.reverse_mapping = {v: k for (k, v) in column_remapping.items()}
2345        new_cols = [k for k in column_remapping.keys()]
2346        orig_cols = [k for k in column_remapping.values()]
2347        unknown = set(orig_cols) - set(source.column_names)
2348        if len(unknown) > 0:
2349            raise ValueError("Tried to rename unknown columns: " + str(unknown))
2350        collisions = (
2351            set(source.column_names) - set(new_cols).intersection(orig_cols)
2352        ).intersection(new_cols)
2353        if len(collisions) > 0:
2354            raise ValueError(
2355                "Mapping "
2356                + str(self.column_remapping)
2357                + " collides with existing columns "
2358                + str(collisions)
2359            )
2360        column_names = [
2361            (k if k not in self.reverse_mapping.keys() else self.reverse_mapping[k])
2362            for k in source.column_names
2363        ]
2364        self.new_columns = set(new_cols) - set(orig_cols)
2365        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2366            self,
2367            column_names=column_names,
2368            sources=[source],
2369            node_name="RenameColumnsNode",
2370        )
2371
2372    def forbidden_columns(
2373        self, *, forbidden: Optional[Set[str]] = None
2374    ) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:

2376        Determine which columns should not be in source tables
2377        (were not in declared structure, and interfere with column production).

2380        :return: dictionary operator keys to forbidden sets.

2386        new_forbidden.update(self.new_columns)
2387        return self.sources[0].forbidden_columns(forbidden=new_forbidden)

2400        return new_sources[0].rename_columns(column_remapping=self.column_remapping)

class NaturalJoinNode(ViewRepresentation): 
2464class NaturalJoinNode(ViewRepresentation):
2465    """
2466    Class representation of .natural_join() method/step.
2467    """
2468
2469    on_a: List[str]
2470    on_b: List[str]
2471    jointype: str
2472
2473    def __init__(
2474        self,
2475        a,
2476        b,
2477        *,
2478        on_a: List[str],
2479        on_b: List[str],
2480        jointype: str,
2481        check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec: bool = False,
2482    ):
2483        # check set of tables is consistent in both sub-dags
2484        a_tables = a.get_tables()
2485        b_tables = b.get_tables()
2486        _assert_tables_defs_consistent(a_tables, b_tables)
2487        assert isinstance(on_a, List)
2488        assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_a])
2489        assert isinstance(on_b, List)
2490        assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_b])
2491        assert len(on_a) == len(on_b)
2492        common_table_keys = set(a_tables.keys()).intersection(b_tables.keys())
2493        for k in common_table_keys:
2494            if not a_tables[k].same_table_description_(b_tables[k]):
2495                raise ValueError(
2496                    "Different definition of table object on a/b for: " + k
2497                )
2498        # check columns
2499        column_names = list(a.column_names)
2500        columns_seen = set(column_names)
2501        for ci in b.column_names:
2502            if ci not in columns_seen:
2503                column_names.append(ci)
2504                columns_seen.add(ci)
2505        missing_left = set(on_a) - set(a.column_names)
2506        if len(missing_left) > 0:
2507            raise KeyError("left table missing join keys: " + str(missing_left))
2508        missing_right = set(on_b) - set(b.column_names)
2509        if len(missing_right) > 0:
2510            raise KeyError("right table missing join keys: " + str(missing_right))
2511        if check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec:
2512            missing_common = (
2513                set(a.column_names).intersection(set(b.column_names)) - set(on_a).intersection(on_b)
2514            )
2515            if len(missing_common) > 0:
2516                raise KeyError(
2517                    "check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec set, and the following common keys are are not in the on-clause: "
2518                    + str(missing_common)
2519                )
2520        # try to re-use column names if possible, saves space in deeply nested join trees.
2521        column_names = tuple(column_names)
2522        if isinstance(a.column_names, tuple) and (
2523            set(column_names) == set(a.column_names)
2524        ):
2525            column_names = a.column_names
2526        elif isinstance(b.column_names, tuple) and (
2527            set(column_names) == set(b.column_names)
2528        ):
2529            column_names = b.column_names
2530        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2531            self,
2532            column_names=column_names,
2533            sources=[a, b],
2534            node_name="NaturalJoinNode",
2535        )
2536        self.on_a = on_a
2537        self.on_b = on_b
2538        self.jointype = data_algebra.expr_rep.standardize_join_type(jointype)
2539        if (self.jointype == "CROSS") and (len(self.on_a) != 0):
2540            raise ValueError("CROSS joins must have an empty 'on' list")
2541
2542    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2543        """
2544        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
2545
2546        :param a: operators to apply to
2547        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
2548        :return: new operator DAG
2549        """
2550        new_sources = [
2551            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
2552        ]
2553        return new_sources[0].natural_join(
2554            b=new_sources[1], on=[(va, vb) for (va, vb) in zip(self.on_a, self.on_b)], jointype=self.jointype
2555        )
2556
2557    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
2558        if not isinstance(other, NaturalJoinNode):
2559            return False
2560        if not self.on_a == other.on_a:
2561            return False
2562        if not self.on_b == other.on_b:
2563            return False
2564        if not self.jointype == other.jointype:
2565            return False
2566        return True
2567
2568    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
2569        """
2570        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
2571
2572        :param using: optional column restriction.
2573        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
2574        """
2575        if using is None:
2576            return [OrderedSet(self.sources[i].column_names) for i in range(2)]
2577        using = using.union(self.on_a).union(self.on_b)
2578        return [
2579            ordered_intersect(self.sources[i].column_names, using) for i in range(2)
2580        ]
2581
2582    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
2583        """
2584        Return text representing operations.
2585
2586        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
2587        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
2588        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
2589        """
2590        s = "_0."
2591        if print_sources:
2592            s = (
2593                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
2594                + "\n"
2595                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
2596            )
2597        s = s + (".natural_join(b=\n" + " " * (indent + 6))
2598        if print_sources:
2599            s = s + (
2600                self.sources[1].to_python_src_(indent=max(indent, 0) + 6, strict=strict)
2601                + ",\n"
2602                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 6)
2603            )
2604        else:
2605            s = s + " _1, "
2606        on_arg = _convert_parallel_lists_to_on_clause(self.on_a, self.on_b)
2607        s = s + (
2608            "on=" + on_arg.__repr__() + ", jointype=" + self.jointype.__repr__() + ")"
2609        )
2610        return s
2611
2612    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
2613        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
2614    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
2615        """
2616        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
2617
2618        :param db_model: database model
2619        :param using: optional column restriction set
2620        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
2621        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
2622        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
2623        """
2624        return db_model.natural_join_to_near_sql(
2625            self,
2626            using=using,
2627            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
2628            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
2629        )

Class representation of .natural_join() method/step.

NaturalJoinNode( a, b, *, on_a: List[str], on_b: List[str], jointype: str, check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec: bool = False) 
2473    def __init__(
2474        self,
2475        a,
2476        b,
2477        *,
2478        on_a: List[str],
2479        on_b: List[str],
2480        jointype: str,
2481        check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec: bool = False,
2482    ):
2483        # check set of tables is consistent in both sub-dags
2484        a_tables = a.get_tables()
2485        b_tables = b.get_tables()
2486        _assert_tables_defs_consistent(a_tables, b_tables)
2487        assert isinstance(on_a, List)
2488        assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_a])
2489        assert isinstance(on_b, List)
2490        assert numpy.all([isinstance(v, str) for v in on_b])
2491        assert len(on_a) == len(on_b)
2492        common_table_keys = set(a_tables.keys()).intersection(b_tables.keys())
2493        for k in common_table_keys:
2494            if not a_tables[k].same_table_description_(b_tables[k]):
2495                raise ValueError(
2496                    "Different definition of table object on a/b for: " + k
2497                )
2498        # check columns
2499        column_names = list(a.column_names)
2500        columns_seen = set(column_names)
2501        for ci in b.column_names:
2502            if ci not in columns_seen:
2503                column_names.append(ci)
2504                columns_seen.add(ci)
2505        missing_left = set(on_a) - set(a.column_names)
2506        if len(missing_left) > 0:
2507            raise KeyError("left table missing join keys: " + str(missing_left))
2508        missing_right = set(on_b) - set(b.column_names)
2509        if len(missing_right) > 0:
2510            raise KeyError("right table missing join keys: " + str(missing_right))
2511        if check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec:
2512            missing_common = (
2513                set(a.column_names).intersection(set(b.column_names)) - set(on_a).intersection(on_b)
2514            )
2515            if len(missing_common) > 0:
2516                raise KeyError(
2517                    "check_all_common_keys_in_equi_spec set, and the following common keys are are not in the on-clause: "
2518                    + str(missing_common)
2519                )
2520        # try to re-use column names if possible, saves space in deeply nested join trees.
2521        column_names = tuple(column_names)
2522        if isinstance(a.column_names, tuple) and (
2523            set(column_names) == set(a.column_names)
2524        ):
2525            column_names = a.column_names
2526        elif isinstance(b.column_names, tuple) and (
2527            set(column_names) == set(b.column_names)
2528        ):
2529            column_names = b.column_names
2530        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2531            self,
2532            column_names=column_names,
2533            sources=[a, b],
2534            node_name="NaturalJoinNode",
2535        )
2536        self.on_a = on_a
2537        self.on_b = on_b
2538        self.jointype = data_algebra.expr_rep.standardize_join_type(jointype)
2539        if (self.jointype == "CROSS") and (len(self.on_a) != 0):
2540            raise ValueError("CROSS joins must have an empty 'on' list")

2639    def __init__(self, a, b, *, id_column="table_name", a_name="a", b_name="b"):
2640        # check set of tables is consistent in both sub-dags
2641        assert isinstance(a, ViewRepresentation)
2642        assert isinstance(b, ViewRepresentation)
2643        a_tables = a.get_tables()

2649                raise ValueError(
2650                    "Different definition of table object on a/b for: " + k
2651                )

2653        # check columns

2655            raise ValueError("a and b should have same set of column names")

2657            raise ValueError("id_column should not be an input table column name")

class ConvertRecordsNode(ViewRepresentation): 
2766class ConvertRecordsNode(ViewRepresentation):
2767    """
2768    Class representation of .convert_records() method/step.
2769    """
2770
2771    def __init__(self, *, source, record_map):
2772        sources = [source]
2773        self.record_map = record_map
2774        unknown = set(self.record_map.columns_needed) - set(source.column_names)
2775        if len(unknown) > 0:
2776            raise ValueError("missing required columns: " + str(unknown))
2777        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2778            self,
2779            column_names=record_map.columns_produced,
2780            sources=sources,
2781            node_name="ConvertRecordsNode",
2782        )
2783
2784    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2785        """
2786        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
2787
2788        :param a: operators to apply to
2789        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
2790        :return: new operator DAG
2791        """
2792        new_sources = [
2793            s.apply_to(a, target_table_key=target_table_key) for s in self.sources
2794        ]
2795        return new_sources[0].convert_records(record_map=self.record_map)
2796
2797    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
2798        if not isinstance(other, ConvertRecordsNode):
2799            return False
2800        if not self.record_map == other.record_map:
2801            return False
2802        return True
2803
2804    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
2805        """
2806        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
2807
2808        :param using: optional column restriction.
2809        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
2810        """
2811        return [self.record_map.columns_needed]
2812
2813    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
2814        """
2815        Return text representing operations.
2816
2817        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
2818        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
2819        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
2820        """
2821        s = ""
2822        if print_sources:
2823            s = (
2824                self.sources[0].to_python_src_(indent=indent, strict=strict)
2825                + "\n"
2826                + " " * (max(indent, 0) + 3)
2827            )
2828        rm_str = self.record_map.__repr__()
2829        rm_str = re.sub("\n", "\n   ", rm_str)
2830        s = s + ".convert_records(" + rm_str
2831        s = s + ")"
2832        return s
2833
2834    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
2835        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
2836    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
2837        """
2838        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
2839
2840        :param db_model: database model
2841        :param using: optional column restriction set
2842        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
2843        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
2844        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
2845        """
2846        if temp_id_source is None:
2847            temp_id_source = [0]
2848        # TODO: narrow to what we are using
2849        # TODO: use nearsql instead of strings / lists of strings
2850        near_sql = self.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
2851            db_model=db_model,
2852            using=None,
2853            temp_id_source=temp_id_source,
2854            sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
2855        )
2856        assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
2857        # claims to use all columns
2858        if self.record_map.blocks_in is not None:
2859            view_name = "convert_records_blocks_in_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
2860            temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
2861            pi, si = db_model.blocks_to_row_recs_query_str_list_pair(
2862                record_spec=self.record_map.blocks_in
2863            )
2864            near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLRawQStep(
2865                prefix=pi,
2866                query_name=view_name,
2867                quoted_query_name=db_model.quote_identifier(view_name),
2868                sub_sql=data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLContainer(near_sql=near_sql),
2869                suffix=si,
2870                annotation="convert records blocks in",
2871                ops_key=None,
2872            )
2873            assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
2874        if self.record_map.blocks_out is not None:
2875            view_name = "convert_records_blocks_out_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
2876            temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
2877            pi, si = db_model.row_recs_to_blocks_query_str_list_pair(
2878                record_spec=self.record_map.blocks_out,
2879            )
2880            near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLRawQStep(
2881                prefix=pi,
2882                query_name=view_name,
2883                quoted_query_name=db_model.quote_identifier(view_name),
2884                sub_sql=data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLContainer(near_sql=near_sql),
2885                suffix=si,
2886                annotation="convert records blocks out",
2887                ops_key=None,
2888            )
2889            assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
2890        return near_sql
