class SQLNode(ViewRepresentation): 
2893class SQLNode(ViewRepresentation):
2894    """
2895    Class representation of user SQL step in pipeline. Can be used to start a pipeline instead of a TableDescription.
2896    """
2897
2898    def __init__(
2899        self, *, sql: Union[str, List[str]], column_names: List[str], view_name: str
2900    ):
2901        if isinstance(sql, str):
2902            sql = sql.splitlines(keepends=False)
2903            sql = [v for v in sql if len(v.strip()) > 0]
2904        assert isinstance(sql, list)
2905        assert len(sql) > 0
2906        assert all([isinstance(v, str) for v in sql])
2907        assert isinstance(view_name, str)
2908        self.sql = sql.copy()
2909        self.view_name = view_name
2910        ViewRepresentation.__init__(
2911            self,
2912            column_names=column_names,
2913            node_name="SQLNode",
2914        )
2915
2916    def apply_to(self, a, *, target_table_key=None):
2917        """
2918        Apply self to operator DAG a. Basic OperatorPlatform, composable API.
2919
2920        :param a: operators to apply to
2921        :param target_table_key: table key to replace with self, None counts as "match all"
2922        :return: new operator DAG
2923        """
2924        return self
2925
2926    def _equiv_nodes(self, other):
2927        if not isinstance(other, SQLNode):
2928            return False
2929        if self.view_name != other.view_name:
2930            return False
2931        if self.column_names != other.column_names:
2932            return False
2933        if self.sql != other.sql:
2934            return False
2935        return True
2936
2937    def get_tables(self):
2938        """Get a dictionary of all tables used in an operator DAG,
2939        raise an exception if the values are not consistent."""
2940        return dict()
2941
2942    def columns_used_from_sources(self, using: Optional[set] = None) -> List:
2943        """
2944        Get columns used from sources. Internal method.
2945
2946        :param using: optional column restriction.
2947        :return: list of order sets (list parallel to sources).
2948        """
2949        return []
2950
2951    def to_python_src_(self, *, indent=0, strict=True, print_sources=True):
2952        """
2953        Return text representing operations.
2954
2955        :param indent: additional indent to apply in formatting.
2956        :param strict: if False allow eliding of columns names and other long structures.
2957        :param print_sources: logical, print children.
2958        """
2959        s = (
2960            "SQLNode(sql="
2961            + str(self.sql)
2962            + ", column_names="
2963            + str(self.column_names)
2964            + ", view_name="
2965            + self.view_name.__repr__()
2966            + ")"
2967        )
2968        return s
2969
2970    def to_near_sql_implementation_(
2971        self, db_model, *, using, temp_id_source, sql_format_options=None
2972    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
2973        """
2974        Convert operator dag into NearSQL type for translation to SQL string.
2975
2976        :param db_model: database model
2977        :param using: optional column restriction set
2978        :param temp_id_source: source of temporary ids
2979        :param sql_format_options: options for sql formatting
2980        :return: data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL
2981        """
2982        quoted_query_name = db_model.quote_identifier(self.view_name)
2983        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLRawQStep(
2984            prefix=self.sql,
2985            query_name=self.view_name,
2986            quoted_query_name=quoted_query_name,
2987            sub_sql=None,
2988            suffix=None,
2989            annotation="user supplied SQL",
2990            add_select=False,
2991            ops_key=None,
2992        )
2993        return near_sql

2996def ex(d, *, data_model=None, narrow=True, allow_limited_tables=False):
2997    """
2998    Evaluate operators with respect to Pandas data frames already stored in the operator chain.

3000    :param d: data algebra pipeline or OpC container to evaluate.

3004    :return: table result

3008    )
